label: Has Realization
definition: b has realization c =Def c realizes b

label: Realizes
definition: (Elucidation) realizes is a relation between a process b and realizable entity c such that c inheres in some d & for all t, if b has participant d then c exists & the type instantiated by b is correlated with the type instantiated by c

label: Participates In
definition: (Elucidation) participates in holds between some b that is either a specifically dependent continuant or generically dependent continuant or independent continuant that is not a spatial region & some process p such that b participates in p some way

label: Has Participant
definition: p has participant c =Def c participates in p

label: Is Concretized By
definition: c is concretized by b =Def b concretizes c

label: Concretizes
definition: b concretizes c =Def b is a process or a specifically dependent continuant & c is a generically dependent continuant & there is some time t such that c is the pattern or content which b shares at t with actual or potential copies

label: Preceded By
definition: b preceded by c =Def b precedes c

label: Precedes
definition: (Elucidation) precedes is a relation between occurrents o, o' such that if t is the temporal extent of o & t' is the temporal extent of o' then either the last instant of o is before the first instant of o' or the last instant of o is the first instant of o' & neither o nor o' are temporal instants

label: Occurs In
definition: b occurs in c =Def b is a process or a process boundary & c is a material entity or site & there exists a spatiotemporal region r & b occupies spatiotemporal region r & for all time t, if b exists at t then c exists at t & there exist spatial regions s and s' where b spatially projects onto s at t & c occupies spatial region s' at t & s is a continuant part of s' at t

label: Generically Depends On
definition: b generically depends on c =Def b is a generically dependent continuant & c is an independent continuant that is not a spatial region & at some time t there inheres in c a specifically dependent continuant which concretizes b at t

label: Is Carrier Of
definition: b is carrier of c =Def there is some time t such that c generically depends on b at t

label: Exists At
definition: (Elucidation) exists at is a relation between a particular and some temporal region at which the particular exists

label: Has Member Part
definition: b has member part c =Def c member part of b

label: Has Occurrent Part
definition: b has occurrent part c =Def c occurrent part of b

label: Has Temporal Part
definition: b has temporal part c =Def c temporal part of b

label: Location Of
definition: b location of c =Def c located in b

label: Material Basis Of
definition: b material basis of c =Def c has material basis b

label: Member Part Of
definition: b member part of c =Def b is an object & c is a material entity & there is some time t such that b continuant part of c at t & there is a mutually exhaustive and pairwise disjoint partition of c into objects x1, ..., xn (for some n ≠ 1) with b = xi (for some 1 <= i <= n)

label: Occurrent Part Of
definition: (Elucidation) occurrent part of is a relation between occurrents b and c when b is part of c

label: Temporal Part Of
definition: b temporal part of c =Def b occurrent part of c & (b and c are temporal regions) or (b and c are spatiotemporal regions & b temporally projects onto an occurrent part of the temporal region that c temporally projects onto) or (b and c are processes or process boundaries & b occupies a temporal region that is an occurrent part of the temporal region that c occupies)

label: Temporally Projects Onto
definition: (Elucidation) temporally projects onto is a relation between a spatiotemporal region s and some temporal region which is the temporal extent of s

label: Located In
definition: b located in c =Def b is an independent continuant & c is an independent & neither is a spatial region & there is some time t such that the spatial region which b occupies at t is continuant part of the spatial region which c occupies at t

label: Continuant Part Of
definition: b continuant part of c =Def b and c are continuants & there is some time t such that b and c exist at t & b part of c at t

label: Has Continuant Part
definition: b has continuant part c =Def c continuant part of b

label: Environs
definition: b environs c =Def c occurs in b

label: History Of
definition: (Elucidation) history of is a relation between history b and material entity c such that b is the unique history of c

label: Has History
definition: b has history c =Def c history of b

label: Specifically Depended On By
definition: b specifically depended on by c =Def c specifically depends on b

label: Specifically Depends On
definition: (Elucidation) specifically depends on is a relation between a specifically dependent continuant b and specifically dependent continuant or independent continuant that is not a spatial region c such that b and c share no parts in common & b is of a nature such that at all times t it cannot exist unless c exists & b is not a boundary of c

label: Bearer Of
definition: b bearer of c =Def c inheres in b

label: Inheres In
definition: b inheres in c =Def b is a specifically dependent continuant & c is an independent continuant that is not a spatial region & b specifically depends on c

label: Occupies Temporal Region
definition: p occupies temporal region t =Def p is a process or process boundary & the spatiotemporal region occupied by p temporally projects onto t

label: Occupies Spatiotemporal Region
definition: (Elucidation) occupies spatiotemporal region is a relation between a process or process boundary p and the spatiotemporal region s which is its spatiotemporal extent

label: Occupies Spatial Region
definition: b occupies spatial region r =Def b is an independent continuant that is not a spatial region & r is a spatial region & there is some time t such that every continuant part of b occupies some continuant part of r at t and no continuant part of b occupies any spatial region that is not a continuant part of r at t

label: Spatially Projects Onto
definition: (Elucidation) spatially projects onto is a relation between some spatiotemporal region b and spatial region c such that at some time t, c is the spatial extent of b at t

label: Has Material Basis
definition: b has material basis c =Def b is a disposition & c is a material entity & there is some d bearer of b & there is some time t such that c is a continuant part of d at t & d has disposition b because c is a continuant part of d at t

label: First Instant Of
definition: t first instant of t' =Def t is a temporal instant & t' is a temporal region t' & t precedes all temporal parts of t' other than t

label: Has First Instant
definition: t has first instant t' =Def t' first instant of t

label: Last Instant Of
definition: t last instant of t' =Def t is a temporal instant & t' is a temporal region & all temporal parts of t' other than t precede t

label: Has Last Instant
definition: t has last instant t' =Def t' last instant of t

label: Entity
definition: (Elucidation) An entity is anything that exists or has existed or will exist

label: Continuant
definition: (Elucidation) A continuant is an entity that persists, endures, or continues to exist through time while maintaining its identity

label: Occurrent
definition: (Elucidation) An occurrent is an entity that unfolds itself in time or it is the start or end of such an entity or it is a temporal or spatiotemporal region

label: Independent Continuant
definition: b is an independent continuant =Def b is a continuant & there is no c such that b specifically depends on c or b generically depends on c

label: Spatial Region
definition: (Elucidation) A spatial region is a continuant entity that is a continuant part of the spatial projection of a portion of spacetime at a given time

label: Temporal Region
definition: (Elucidation) A temporal region is an occurrent over which processes can unfold

label: Two-dimensional Spatial Region
definition: (Elucidation) A two-dimensional spatial region is a spatial region that is a whole consisting of a surface together with zero or more surfaces which may have spatial regions of lower dimension as parts

label: Spatiotemporal Region
definition: (Elucidation) A spatiotemporal region is an occurrent that is an occurrent part of spacetime

label: Process
definition: (Elucidation) p is a process means p is an occurrent that has some temporal proper part and for some time t, p has some material entity as participant

label: Disposition
definition: (Elucidation) A disposition b is a realizable entity such that if b ceases to exist then its bearer is physically changed & b's realization occurs when and because this bearer is in some special physical circumstances & this realization occurs in virtue of the bearer's physical make-up

label: Realizable Entity
definition: (Elucidation) A realizable entity is a specifically dependent continuant that inheres in some independent continuant which is not a spatial region & which is of a type some instances of which are realized in processes of a correlated type

label: Zero-dimensional Spatial Region
definition: (Elucidation) A zero-dimensional spatial region is one or a collection of more than one spatially disjoint points in space

label: Quality
definition: (Elucidation) A quality is a specifically dependent continuant that, in contrast to roles and dispositions, does not require any further process in order to be realized

label: Specifically Dependent Continuant
definition: b is a specifically dependent continuant =Def b is a continuant & there is some independent continuant c which is not a spatial region & which is such that b specifically depends on c

label: Role
definition: (Elucidation) A role b is a realizable entity such that b exists because there is some single bearer that is in some special physical, social, or institutional set of circumstances in which this bearer does not have to be & b is not such that, if it ceases to exist, then the physical make-up of the bearer is thereby changed

label: Fiat Object Part
definition: (Elucidation) A fiat object part b is a material entity & such that if b exists then it is continuant part of some object c & demarcated from the remainder of c by one or more fiat surfaces

label: One-dimensional Spatial Region
definition: (Elucidation) A one-dimensional spatial region is a whole consisting of a line together with zero or more lines which may have points as parts

label: Object Aggregate
definition: (Elucidation) An object aggregate is a material entity consisting exactly of a plurality (≥1) of objects as member parts which together form a unit

label: Three-dimensional Spatial Region
definition: (Elucidation) A three-dimensional spatial region is a whole consisting of a spatial volume together with zero or more spatial volumes which may have spatial regions of lower dimension as parts

label: Site
definition: (Elucidation) A site is a three-dimensional immaterial entity whose boundaries either (partially or wholly) coincide with the boundaries of one or more material entities or have locations determined in relation to some material entity

label: Object
definition: (Elucidation) An object is a material entity which manifests causal unity & is of a type instances of which are maximal relative to the sort of causal unity manifested

label: Generically Dependent Continuant
definition: (Elucidation) A generically dependent continuant is an entity that exists in virtue of the fact that there is at least one of what may be multiple copies which is the content or the pattern that multiple copies would share

label: Function
definition: (Elucidation) A function is a disposition that exists in virtue of its bearer's physical make-up & this physical make-up is something the bearer possesses because it came into being either through evolution (in the case of natural biological entities) or through intentional design (in the case of artefacts) in order to realize processes of a certain sort

label: Process Boundary
definition: p is a process boundary =Def p is a temporal part of a process & p has no proper temporal parts

label: One-dimensional Temporal Region
definition: (Elucidation) A one-dimensional temporal region is a temporal region that is a whole that has a temporal interval and zero or more temporal intervals and temporal instants as parts

label: Material Entity
definition: (Elucidation) A material entity is an independent continuant that at all times at which it exists has some portion of matter as continuant part

label: Continuant Fiat Boundary
definition: (Elucidation) A continuant fiat boundary b is an immaterial entity that is of zero, one or two dimensions & such that there is no time t when b has a spatial region as continuant part & whose location is determined in relation to some material entity

label: Immaterial Entity
definition: b is an immaterial entity =Def b is an independent continuant which is such that there is no time t when it has a material entity as continuant part

label: Fiat Line
definition: (Elucidation) A fiat line is a one-dimensional continuant fiat boundary that is continuous

label: Relational Quality
definition: b is a relational quality =Def b is a quality & there exists c and d such that c and d are not identical & b specifically depends on c & b specifically depends on d

label: Fiat Surface
definition: (Elucidation) A fiat surface is a two-dimensional continuant fiat boundary that is self-connected

label: Fiat Point
definition: (Elucidation) A fiat point is a zero-dimensional continuant fiat boundary that consists of a single point

label: Zero-dimensional Temporal Region
definition: (Elucidation) A zero-dimensional temporal region is a temporal region that is a whole consisting of one or more separated temporal instants as parts

label: History
definition: (Elucidation) A history is a process that is the sum of the totality of processes taking place in the spatiotemporal region occupied by the material part of a material entity

label: Temporal Interval
definition: (Elucidation) A temporal interval is a one-dimensional temporal region that is continuous, thus without gaps or breaks

label: Temporal Instant
definition: (Elucidation) A temporal instant is a zero-dimensional temporal region that has no proper temporal part

label: Query Text
definition: The text of a query that is associated with a class

label: Doctrinal Definition
definition: A Definition that is taken directly from a Doctrinal Source.

label: Si Unit Label
definition: An Alternative Label that is officially accepted for use in the International System of Units (SI) as denoting a Measurement Unit.

label: Ordinal Measurement Annotation
definition: An ordinal measurement value of an instance of a quality, realizable or process profile

label: Si Unit Symbol
definition: An Acronym that is officially accepted for use in the International System of Units (SI) as denoting a Measurement Unit.

label: Nominal Measurement Annotation
definition: A nominal measurement value of an instance of a quality, realizable or process profile

label: Term Creator
definition: The name of the Term Editor who added the term to the ontology.

label: Content License
definition: The name and description of the license under which the ideas, concepts and other informational content expressed in the .owl file are released.

label: Copyright
definition: An assertion of copyright

label: Doctrinal Source
definition: A Definition Source that consists of a formalized doctrine in which the term is authoritatively defined.

label: Measurement Annotation
definition: A measurement value of an instance of a quality, realizable or process profile

label: Ratio Measurement Annotation
definition: A ratio measurement value of an instance of a quality, realizable or process profile

label: Doctrinal Label
definition: An Alternative Label that consists of the preferred term or phrase used by a Doctrinal Source to denote the entity.

label: Doctrinal Acronym
definition: An Acronym that is used by a Doctrinal Source to denote the entity.

label: Has Token Unit
definition: A relation between an information content entity and a widely used measurement unit of the token used to express it.

label: Acronym
definition: An Alternative Label that consists of a shortened or abbreviated form of the rdfs:label and is used to denote the entity.

label: Definition Source
definition: A citation of where all or some of the information used to create the term's Definition was acquired from.

label: Interval Measurement Annotation
definition: A interval measurement value of an instance of a quality, realizable or process profile

label: Designator Annotation
definition: A name or other identifier that is used to designate an individual.

label: Http Query String
definition: The text of an HTTP request that can be sent to a SPARQL Protocol service.

label: Code License
definition: The name and description of the license under which the .owl file is released.

label: Is Curated In Ontology
definition: An annotation property that links a class, property, or named individual to the URI of the ontology where it is located.

label: Is Tokenized By
definition: A relation between an information content entity and a widely used token used to express it.

label: Term Editor
definition: The name of a person who contributed to the development or enhancement of the term.

label: Bearer Of

label: Inheres In
definition: b inheres in c =Def b is a specifically dependent continuant & c is an independent continuant that is not a spatial region & b specifically depends on c

label: Occupies Temporal Region

label: Occupies Spatiotemporal Region
definition: (Elucidation) occupies spatiotemporal region is a relation between a process or process boundary p and the spatiotemporal region s which is its spatiotemporal extent

label: Occupies Spatial Region
definition: b occupies spatial region r =Def b is an independent continuant that is not a spatial region & r is a spatial region & there is some time t such that every continuant part of b occupies some continuant part of r at t and no continuant part of b occupies any spatial region that is not a continuant part of r at t

label: Spatially Projects Onto
definition: (Elucidation) spatially projects onto is a relation between some spatiotemporal region b and spatial region c such that at some time t, c is the spatial extent of b at t

label: Has Material Basis
definition: b has material basis c =Def b is a disposition & c is a material entity & there is some d bearer of b & there is some time t such that c is a continuant part of d at t & d has disposition b because c is a continuant part of d at t

label: First Instant Of
definition: t first instant of t' =Def t is a temporal instant & t' is a temporal region t' & t precedes all temporal parts of t' other than t

label: Has First Instant
definition: t has first instant t' =Def t' first instant of t

label: Last Instant Of
definition: t last instant of t' =Def t is a temporal instant & t' is a temporal region & all temporal parts of t' other than t precede t

label: Has Last Instant
definition: t has last instant t' =Def t' last instant of t

label: Is Successor Of
definition: A continuant c2 is a successor of some continuant c1 iff there is some process p1 and c1 is an input to p1 and c2 is an output of p1. Inverse of is predecessor.

label: Has Process Part
definition: x has_process_part y iff x and y are instances of Process, such that y occurs during the temporal interval of x, and y either provides an input to x or receives an output of x, or both.

label: Has Object
definition: If p is a process and c is a continuant, then p has object c if and only if p is performed by an agent and c is part of the projected state that agent intends to achieve by performing p.

label: Has Inside Instant
definition: For Temporal Interval t1 and Temporal Instant t2, t1 has inside instant t2 if and only if there exists Temporal Instants t3 and t4 that are part of t1 and non-identical with t2, such that t3 is before t2 and t4 is after t2.

label: Has All Members Located In
definition: x has all members located in y iff x is an instance of Object Aggregate and y is an instance of independent continuant but not a spatial region, and every member of x is located in y.

label: Agent In
definition: x agent_in y iff y is an instance of Process and x is an instance of Agent, such that x is causally active in y.

label: Coincides With
definition: An immaterial entity im1 coincides with some immaterial entity im2 iff im1 is a spatial part of im2 and im2 is a spatial part of im1.

label: Has Subsidiary
definition: An Organization o1 has_subsidiary Organization o2 iff o1 controls o2 by having the capacity to determine the outcome of decisions about o2's financial and operating policies.

label: Has Inside Interval
definition: A Temporal Interval INT2 has inside interval some Temporal Interval INT1 iff there exist Temporal Instants inst1, inst2, inst3, and inst4 such that inst1 is the starting instant of INT1, inst2 is the ending instant of INT1, inst3 is the starting instant of INT2, inst4 is the ending instant of INT2, inst3 is before inst1, and inst2 is before inst4.

label: Tangential Part Of
definition: An immaterial entity im1 is a tangential part of some immaterial entity im2 iff im1 is a spatial part of im2 and there exists some immaterial entity im3 such that im3 externally connects with im1 and im3 externally connects with im2.

label: Partially Overlaps With
definition: An immaterial entity im1 partially overlaps with some immaterial entity im2 iff im1 overlaps with im2 and im1 is not a spatial part of im2 and im2 is not a spatial part of im1.

label: Is Supervised By
definition: A person p1 is supervised by a person p2 by virtue of p1 being directed, managed, or overseen by p2.

label: Role Of Aggregate
definition: x role_of_aggregate y iff y is an instance of Object Aggregate and x is an instance of Role, and x inheres_in_aggregate y.

label: Prohibits
definition: x prohibits y at t iff: x is an instance of Process Regulation at time t, and y is an instance of Process at time t, and x prescribes that some y must not occur.

label: Is Subject Of
definition: A primitive relationship between an instance of an Entity and an instance of an Information Content Entity.

label: Is Cause Of
definition: x is_cause_of y iff x and y are instances of Occurrent, and y is a consequence of x.

label: Is Disrupted By
definition: Inverse of disrupts.

label: Is Required By
definition: y is_required_by x at t iff: x is an instance of Process Regulation at time t, and y is an instance of Process at time t, and x prescribes that y must occur.

label: Is About
definition: A primitive relationship between an Information Content Entity and some Entity.

label: Inheres In Aggregate
definition: x inheres_in_aggregate y iff x is an instance of Specifically Dependent Continuant and y is an instance of Object Aggregate and z is an instance of Object, such that z bearer_of x, and all other members of y are bearers of a unique instance of the same type as x.

label: Connected With
definition: An immaterial entity im1 is connected with some immaterial entity im2 iff there exists some immaterial entity im3 that is common to both im1 and im2.

label: Is A Ordinal Measurement Of
definition: x is_a_ordinal_measurement_of y iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x describes some attribute of y relative to a scale ordered by rank.

label: Uses
definition: x uses y iff x is an instance of an Agent and y is an instance of a Material Entity, such that both x and y participate in some instance of a Process wherein x attempts to accomplish a goal by manipulating, deploying, or leveraging some attribute of y.

label: Interval Finishes
definition: A Temporal Interval INT1 finishes some Temporal Interval INT2 iff there exists Temporal Instants inst1, inst2, and inst3 such that inst 1 is the starting instant of INT1, inst2 is the ending instant of both INT1 and INT2, inst3 is the starting instant of INT2, and inst3 is before inst1.

label: Is Subsidiary Of
definition: An Organization o2 is_subsidiary_of Organization o1 iff o1 controls o2 by having the capacity to determine the outcome of decisions about o2's financial and operating policies.

label: Is Output Of
definition: x is_output_of y iff x is an instance of Continuant and y is an instance of Process, such that the presence of x at the end of y is a necessary condition for the completion of y.

label: Is Prohibited By
definition: y is_prohibited_by y at t iff: x is an instance of Process Regulation at time t, and y is an instance of Process at time t, and x prescribes that y must not occur.

label: Caused By
definition: x caused_by y iff x and y are instances of Occurrent, and x is a consequence of y.

label: Interval Finished By
definition: A Temporal Interval INT2 is finished by some Temporal Interval INT1 iff there exists Temporal Instants inst1, inst2, and inst3 such that inst 1 is the starting instant of INT1, inst2 is the ending instant of both INT1 and INT2, inst3 is the starting instant of INT2, and inst3 is before inst1.

label: Interval Equals
definition: A Temporal Interval INT1 is equal to some Temporal Interval INT2 iff there exists Temporal Instants inst1 and inst2 such that inst1 is the starting instant of both INT1 and INT2 and inst2 is the ending instant of both INT1 and INT2.

label: Is Excerpted From
definition: An Information Bearing Entity b1 is excerpted from another Information Bearing Entity B2 iff b1 is part of some Information Bearing Entity B1 that is carrier of some Information Content Entity C1, B2 is carrier of some Information Content Entity C2, C1 is not identical with C2, b1 is carrier of some Information Content Entity c1, b2 is an Information Bearing Entity that is part of B2 and b2 is carrier of c1 (i.e. the same Information Content Entity as borne by b1).

label: Interval Overlaps
definition: A Temporal Interval INT1 overlaps some Temporal Interval INT2 iff there exist Temporal Instants inst1, inst2, inst3, inst4 such that inst1 is the starting instant of INT1, inst2 is the ending instant of INT1, inst3 is the starting instant of INT2, inst4 is the ending instant of INT2, inst1 is before inst3, inst3 is before inst2, and inst2 is before inst4.

label: Nontangential Part Of
definition: An immaterial entity im1 is a nontangential part of some immaterial entity im2 iff im1 is a spatial part of im2 and there does not exist an immaterial entity im3 such that im3 externally connects with im1 and im3 externally connects with im2.

label: Disposition Of Aggregate
definition: x disposition_of_aggregate y iff y is an instance of Object Aggregate and x is an instance of Disposition, and x inheres_in_aggregate y.

label: Has Accomplice
definition: A Processual Entity p1 has_accomplice some agent a1 iff a1 assists in the commission of p1, is located at the location of p1, but is not agent_in p1.

label: Is Subordinate Role To
definition: For all x,y,t: y is subordinate role to x at t iff: x is an instance of Role at time t, and y is an instance of Role at time t, and there is some z such that x is realized by z and z is an instance of Process which creates, modifies, transfers, or eliminates some u such that u is a Process Regulation at time t, and u is addressed to the bearer of y.

label: Has Some Member Located In
definition: x has some member located in y iff x is an instance of Object Aggregate and y is an instance of independent continuant but not a spatial region, and at least one member of x is located in y.

label: Has Agent
definition: x has_agent y iff x is an instance of Process and y is an instance of Agent, such that y is causally active in x.

label: Affects
definition: x affects y iff x is an instance of Process and y is an instance of Continuant, and x influences y in some manner, most often by producing a change in y.

label: Aggregate Bearer Of
definition: x aggregate_bearer_of y iff x is an instance of Object Aggregate and y is an instance of Specifically Dependent Continuant and z is an instance of Object, such that z bearer of y, and all other members of x are bearers of a unique instance of the same type as y.

label: Time Zone Identifier Used By
definition: x time_zone_identifier_used_by y iff y is an instance of Information Bearing Entity and x is an instance of Time Zone Identifier, such that x designates the spatial region associated with the time zone mentioned in y.

label: Disconnected With
definition: An immaterial entity im1 is disconnected with some immaterial entity im2 iff there does not exist some immaterial entity im3 that is common to both im1 and im2.

label: Is Input Of
definition: x is_input_of y iff x is an instance of Continuant and y is an instance of Process, such that the presence of x at the beginning of y is a necessary condition for the start of y.

label: Is Paternal First Cousin Of
definition: Person A is paternal first cousin of Person B iff Person B has father F and F has sibling P and P is parent of Person A.

label: Has Sender
definition: y has_sender x iff x is an instance of Agent and y is an instance of Act Of Communication, such that x is the initiator and encoder of the InformationContentEntity intended for communication in y.

label: Is Site Of
definition: x is_site_of y iff x is an instance of Site and y is an instance of Process, such that y occurs in x.

label: Is Organizational Context Of
definition: x is_organizational_context_of y iff x is an instance of an Organization and y is an instance of a Role and z is an instance of a Person, such that z's affiliation with x is a prerequisite for z bearing y, or x ascribes y to the bearer of y.

label: Interval Is After
definition: A TemporalInterval INT2 is after some TemporalInterval INT1 iff there exists TemporalInstants inst2, inst1 such that inst2 is the starting instant of INT2 and inst1 is the ending instant of INT1 and inst2 is after inst1.

label: Is Inside Instant Of
definition: For Temporal Instant t1 and Temporal Interval t2, t1 is inside instant of t2 if and only if there are Temporal Instants t3 and t4 non-identical to t1 and part of t2 such that t3 is before t1 and t4 is after t1.

label: Accessory In
definition: y is_accessory_in x iff x is an instance of Process and y is an instance of Agent, such that y assists another agent in the commission of x, and y was not located at the location of x when x occurred, and y was not an agent_in x.

label: Has Spatial Part
definition: y has_spatial_part x iff x, y, z, and q are instances of Immaterial Entity, such that for any z connected with x, z is also connected with y, and q is connected with y but not connected with x.

label: Is Part Of Process
definition: x is_part_of_process y iff x and y are instances of Process, such that x occurs during the temporal interval of y, and x either provides an input to y or receives an output of y.

label: Is Delimited By
definition: An instance of Organization o1 is_delimited_by some Delimiting Domain dd1 iff dd1 is the area within which o1 can legally operate.

label: Is Material Of
definition: An object m is material of an object o when m is the material of which o consists and that material does not undergo a change of kind during the creation of o

label: Interval Disjoint
definition: A Temporal Interval INT1 is disjoint with a Temporal Interval INT2 iff INT1 is before or meets INT2 OR INT2 is before or meets INT1. In other words, INT1 and INT2 are disjoint iff INT1 and INT2 do not overlap, contain, or equal one another.

label: Uses Measurement Unit
definition: y uses_measurement_unit x iff y is an instance of Information Bearing Entity and x is an instance of Measurement Unit, such that x describes the magnitude of measured physical quantity mentioned in y.

label: Delimits
definition: An instance of Delimiting Domain dd1 delimits some Organization o1 iff dd1 is the area within which o1 can legally operate.

label: Has Familial Relationship To
definition: A relationship between persons by virtue of ancestry or legal union.

label: Is Interest Of
definition: The inverse of has_interest_in.

label: Is A Nominal Measurement Of
definition: x is_a_nominal_measurement_of y iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x classifies y relative to some set of shared, possibly arbitrary, characteristics.

label: Interval During
definition: A Temporal Interval INT1 is during some Temporal Interval INT2 iff there exist Temporal Instants inst1, inst2, inst3, and inst4 such that inst1 is the starting instant of INT1, inst2 is the ending instant of INT1, inst3 is the starting instant of INT2, inst4 is the ending instant of INT2, inst3 is before inst1, and inst2 is before inst4.

label: Interval Overlapped By
definition: A Temporal Interval INT2 is overlapped by some Temporal Interval INT1 iff there exist Temporal Instants inst1, inst2, inst3, inst4 such that inst1 is the starting instant of INT1, inst2 is the ending instant of INT1, inst3 is the starting instant of INT2, inst4 is the ending instant of INT2, inst1 is before inst3, inst3 is before inst2, and inst2 is before inst4.

label: Represented By
definition: y represented_by x iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity, and y is an instance of Entity, and z is carrier of x, such that x is about y in virtue of there existing an isomorphism between characteristics of z and y.

label: Is Temporal Region Of
definition: t is temporal region of p iff p occupies temporal region t.

label: Interval Started By
definition: A Temporal Interval INT2 is started by some Temporal Interval INT1 iff there exist Temporal Instants inst1, inst2, and inst3 such that inst1 is the starting instant of both INT1 and INT2, inst2 is the ending instant of INT1, inst3 is the ending instant of INT2 and inst2 is before inst3.

label: Is A Interval Measurement Of
definition: x is_a_interval_measurement_of y iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x describes some attribute of y relative to a scale which has uniform intervals but has a zero value that does not correspond to an absence of the attribute being measured.

label: Is Mention Of
definition: x is_mention_of y iff x is an instance Information Bearing Entity and y is an instance Entity, such that x is used as a reference to y.

label: Designated By
definition: x designated_by y iff y is an instance of Information Content Entity and x is an instance of Entity, such that given some context, y uniquely distinguishes x from other entities.

label: Capability Of Aggregate
definition: x capability_of_aggregate y iff y is an instance of Object Aggregate and x is an instance of Agent Capability, such that x inheres in aggregate y.

label: Condition Described By
definition: c condition_described_by p iff p is an instance of a Performance Specification, and p has part d, and d is an instance of a Descriptive Information Content Entity, and p prescribes an entity s, and d describes c, and c is an entity that is causally relevant to s existing as prescribed by p.

label: Is Affected By
definition: x is_affected_by y iff x is an instance of Continuant and y is an instance of Process, and y influences x in some manner, most often by producing a change in x.

label: Disrupts
definition: A relation where one process disrupts another process from occurring as it would have.

label: Capability Of
definition: x capability_of y iff y is an instance of Agent and x is an instance of Agent Capability, such that x inheres in y.

label: Instant Is After
definition: A temporal instant t2 (a instance of a zero-dimensional temporal region) is after another temporal instant t1 iff there exists some instance of a temporal interval ti1 such that t1 is the starting instant of ti1 and t2 is the ending instant of ti1.

label: Accomplice In
definition: An agent a1 is accomplice_in some Processual Entity p1 iff a1 assists in the commission of p1, is located at the location of p1, but is not agent_in p1.

label: Interval Meets
definition: A Temporal Interval INT1 meets some Temporal Interval INT2 iff there exists some Temporal Instant inst1 such that inst1 is the ending instant of INT1 and inst1 is the starting instant of INT2.

label: Aggregate Has Capability
definition: x aggregate_has_capability y iff x is an instance of Object Aggregate and y is an instance of Agent Capability, such that x is aggregate bearer of y.

label: Language Used In
definition: x language_used_by y iff y is an instance of Information Bearing Entity and x is an instance of Language, such that the literal value of y is a string that is encoded according to the syntax of x.

label: Is Geospatial Coordinate Reference System Of
definition: x is_geospatial_coordinate_reference_system_of y iff y is an instance of Information Bearing Entity and x is an instance of Geospatial Coordinate Reference System, such that x describes the set of standards mentioned in y.

label: Aggregate Has Role
definition: x aggregate_has_role y iff x is an instance of Object Aggregate and y is an instance of Role, such that x aggregate_bearer_of y.

label: Is Measured By
definition: y is_measured_by x iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x describes some attribute of y relative to some scale or classification scheme.

label: Is Maternal First Cousin Of
definition: Person A is maternal first cousin of Person B iff Person B has mother M and M has sibling P and P is parent of Person A.

label: Aggregate Has Quality
definition: x aggregate_has_quality y iff x is an instance of Object Aggregate and y is an instance of Quality, such that x aggregate_bearer_of y.

label: Uses Time Zone Identifier
definition: x uses_time_zone_identifier y iff x is an instance of Information Bearing Entity and y is an instance of Time Zone Identifier, such that y designates the spatial region associated with the time zone mentioned in x.

label: Has Tangential Part
definition: x has_tangential_part y iff x, y, and z are instances of Immaterial Entity, and x has_spatial_part y, such that z externally connects with both x and y.

label: Permits
definition: x permits y at t iff: x is an instance of Process Regulation at time t, and y is an instance of Process at time t, and x prescribes that y may occur.

label: Uses Reference System
definition: y uses_reference_system x iff y is an instance of Information Bearing Entity and x is an instance of Reference System, such that x describes the set of standards mentioned in y.

label: Uses Geospatial Coordinate Reference System
definition: y uses_geospatial_coordinate_reference_system x iff y is an instance of Information Bearing Entity and x is an instance of Geospatial Coordinate Reference System, such that x describes the set of standards mentioned in y.

label: Is Measured By Nominal
definition: y is_measured_by_nominal x iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x classifies y relative to some set of shared, possibly arbitrary, characteristics.

label: Interval Met By
definition: A Temporal Interval INT2 is met by some Temporal Interval INT1 iff there exists some Temporal Instant inst1 such that inst1 is the starting instant of INT2 and inst1 is the ending instant of INT1.

label: Designates
definition: x designates y iff x is an instance of an Information Content Entity, and y is an instance of an Entity, such that given some context, x uniquely distinguishes y from other entities.

label: Described By
definition: x described_by y iff y is an instance of Information Content Entity, and x is an instance of Entity, such that y is about the characteristics by which y can be recognized or visualized.

label: Occurs At
definition: x occurs_at y iff x is an instance of Process and y is an instance of Site, such that x occurs in y.

label: Is Mentioned By
definition: y is_mention_by x iff x is an instance Information Bearing Entity and y is an instance Entity, such that x is used as a reference to y.

label: Prescribed By
definition: x prescribed_by y iff y is an instance of Information Content Entity and x is an instance of Entity, such that y serves as a rule or guide for x if x is an Occurrent, or y serves as a model for x if x is a Continuant.

label: Has Input
definition: y has_input x iff x is an instance of Continuant and y is an instance of Process, such that the presence of x at the beginning of y is a necessary condition for the start of y.

label: Has Recipient
definition: x has_recipient y iff y is an instance of Agent and x is an instance of Act Of Communication, such that y is the recipient and decoder of the InformationContentEntity intended for communication in x.

label: Interval Starts
definition: A Temporal Interval INT1 starts some Temporal Interval INT2 iff there exist Temporal Instants inst1, inst2, and inst3 such that inst1 is the starting instant of both INT1 and INT2, inst2 is the ending instant of INT1, inst3 is the ending instant of INT2 and inst2 is before inst3.

label: Interval Contains
definition: A Temporal Interval INT2 contains some Temporal Interval INT1 iff there exist Temporal Instants inst1, inst2, inst3, and inst4 such that inst1 is the starting instant of INT1, inst2 is the ending instant of INT1, inst3 is the starting instant of INT2, inst4 is the ending instant of INT2, inst3 is before or identical to inst1, and inst2 is before or identical to inst4, but it is not the case that both inst3 is identical to inst1 and inst2 is identical to inst4.

label: Is Used By
definition: x is_used_by y iff y is an instance of an Agent and x is an instance of a Material Entity, such that both x and y participate in some instance of a Process wherein y attempts to accomplish a goal by manipulating, deploying, leveraging some attribute of y.

label: Is Predecessor Of
definition: A continuant c1 is a predecessor of some continuant c2 iff there is some process p1 and c1 is an input to p1 and c2 is an output of p1.

label: Externally Connects With
definition: An immaterial entity im1 externally connects with some immaterial entity im2 iff im1 connects with im2 and im1 does not overlap with im2.

label: Process Starts
definition: x process_starts y iff x and y are instances of processes, and x is_cause_of y, and i is an instance of a temporal instant, and r is an instant of a temporal interval, and y has starting instance i, and x occurs on r, and r interval contains i.

label: Is Object Of
definition: If p is a process and c is a continuant, then c is object of p if and only if the c is part of the projected state that the agent intends to achieve by performing p.

label: Represents
definition: x represents y iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity, y is an instance of Entity, and z is carrier of x, such that x is about y in virtue of there existing an isomorphism between characteristics of z and y.

label: Is Affiliated With
definition: x is_affiliated_with y iff x and y are instances of Agent, such that they have any kind of social or business relationship.

label: Has Affiliate
definition: x is_affiliated_with y iff x and y are instances of Agent, such that they have any kind of social or business relationship.

label: Interval Is Before
definition: A TemporalInterval INT1 is before some TemporalInterval INT2 iff there exists TemporalInstants inst1, inst2 such that inst1 is the ending instant of INT1 and inst2 is the starting instant of INT2 and inst1 is before inst2.

label: Prescribes
definition: x prescribes y iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x serves as a rule or guide for y if y an Occurrent, or x serves as a model for y if y is a Continuant.

label: Supervises
definition: A person p1 supervises a person p2 by virtue of p1 directing, managing, or overseeing p2.

label: Spatial Part Of
definition: x spatial_part_of y iff x, y, z, and q are instances of Immaterial Entity, such that for any z connected with x, z is also connected with y, and q is connected with y but not connected with x.

label: Quality Of Aggregate
definition: x quality_of_aggregate y iff y is an instance of Object Aggregate and x is an instance of Quality, and x inheres_in_aggregate y.

label: Has Accessory
definition: x has_accessory y iff x is an instance of Process and y is an instance of Agent, such that y assists another agent in the commission of x, and y was not located at the location of x when x occurred, and y was not an agent_in x.

label: Has Subordinate Role
definition: For all x,y,t: x has subordinate role y at t iff: x is an instance of Role at time t, and y is an instance of Role at time t, and there is some z such that x is realized by z and z is an instance of Process which creates, modifies, transfers, or eliminates some u such that u is a Process Regulation at time t, and u is addressed to the bearer of y.

label: Has Capability
definition: x has_capability y iff x is an instance of Agent and y is an instance of Agent Capability, such that x bearer of y.

label: Aggregate Has Disposition
definition: x aggregate_has_disposition y iff x is an instance of Object Aggregate and y is an instance of Disposition, such that x aggregate_bearer_of y.

label: Inhibits
definition: x inhibits y iff x and y are non-identical Processes, d is a Decrease of Realizable Entity, and x is_cause_of d, and r is a Realizable Entity, and d has_participant r, and r realized_in y.

label: Is Measurement Unit Of
definition: x is_measurement_unit_of y iff y is an instance of Information Bearing Entity and x is an instance of Measurement Unit, such that x describes the magnitude of measured physical quantity mentioned in y.

label: Process Started By
definition: x process_started_by y iff x and y are instances of processes, and x is caused_by y, and i is an instance of a temporal instant, and r is an instant of a temporal interval, and x has starting instance i, and y occurs on r, and r interval contains i.

label: Is Measured By Ordinal
definition: y is_measured_by_ordinal x iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x describes some attribute of y relative to a scale ordered by rank.

label: Is Measured By Interval
definition: y is_measured_by_interval x iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x describes some attribute of y relative to a scale which has uniform intervals but has a zero value that does not correspond to an absence of the attribute being measured.

label: Is Measured By Ratio
definition: y is_measured_by_ratio x iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x describes some attribute of y relative to a scale having equal unit values and a zero value that corresponds to the absence of the attribute being measured.

label: Is A Measurement Of
definition: x is_a_measurement_of y iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x describes some attribute of y relative to some scale or classification scheme.

label: Inhibited By
definition: y inhibited_by x iff x and y are non-identical Processes, d is a Decrease of Realizable Entity, and x is_cause_of d, and r is a Realizable Entity, and d has_participant r, and r realized_in y.

label: Interval Contained By
definition: A Temporal Interval INT1 is contained by some Temporal Interval INT2 iff there exist Temporal Instants inst1, inst2, inst3, and inst4 such that inst1 is the starting instant of INT1, inst2 is the ending instant of INT1, inst3 is the starting instant of INT2, inst4 is the ending instant of INT2, inst3 is before or identical to inst1, inst2 is before or identical to inst4, and it is not the case that both inst3 is identical to inst1 and inst2 is identical to inst4.

label: Requires
definition: x requires y at t iff: x is an instance of Process Regulation at time t, and y is an instance of Process at time t, and x prescribes that some y must occur.

label: Uses Language
definition: x uses_language y iff x is an instance of an Information Bearing Entity and y is an instance of a Language such that the literal value of x is a string that is encoded according to the syntax of y.

label: Receives
definition: x receives y iff x is an instance of Agent and y is an instance of Act Of Communication, such that x is the recipient and decoder of the InformationContentEntity intended for communication in y.

label: Describes Condition
definition: p describes_condition c iff p is an instance of a Performance Specification, and p has part d, and d is an instance of a Descriptive Information Content Entity, and p prescribes an entity s, and d describes c, and c is an entity that is causally relevant to s existing as prescribed by p.

label: Describes
definition: x describes y iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity, and y is an instance of Entity, such that x is about the characteristics by which y can be recognized or visualized.

label: Is A Ratio Measurement Of
definition: x is_a_ratio_measurement_of y iff x is an instance of Information Content Entity and y is an instance of Entity, such that x describes some attribute of y relative to a scale having equal unit values and a zero value that corresponds to the absence of the attribute being measured.

label: Has Interest In
definition: A relation between an entity and some process where the entity has an interest in that process.

label: Has Output
definition: y has_output x iff x is an instance of Continuant and y is an instance of Process, such that the presence of x at the end of y is a necessary condition for the completion of y.

label: Has Nontangential Part
definition: x has_nontangential_part y iff x and y are instances of Immaterial Entity, and x has_spatial_part y, such that there does not exist another instance of an Immaterial Entity which externally connects with both x and y.

label: Instant Is Before
definition: A temporal instant t1 (a instance of a zero-dimensional temporal region) is before another temporal instant t2 iff there exists some instance of a temporal interval ti1 such that t1 is the starting instant of ti1 and t2 is the ending instant of ti1.

label: Is Made Of
definition: An object o is made of an object m when m is the material that o consists of and that material does not undergo a change of kind during the creation of o

label: Has Organizational Context
definition: x has_organizational_context y iff y is an instance of an Organization and x is an instance of a Role and z is an instance of a Person, such that z's affiliation with y is a prerequisite for z bearing x or y ascribes x to the bearer of x.

label: Sends
definition: x sends y iff x is an instance of Agent and y is an instance of Act Of Communication, such that x is the initiator and encoder of the InformationContentEntity intended for communication in y.

label: Is Reference System Of
definition: x is_reference_system_of y iff y is an instance of Information Bearing Entity and x is an instance of Reference System, such that x describes the set of standards mentioned in y.

label: Is Permitted By
definition: y is_permitted_by x at t iff: x is an instance of Process Regulation at time t, and y is an instance of Process at time t, and x prescribes that y may occur.

label: As Wkt
definition: A Data Property that has as its range a string formated according to the Well-known text standardization for geometric objects.

label: Has Longitude Value
definition: A Data Property that has as its range the longitude value from some Geospatial Location coordinates set expressed in decimal degrees.

label: Has Text Value
definition: A data property that has as its range a string value.

label: Has Latitude Value
definition: A Data Property that has as its range the latitude value from some Geospatial Location coordinates set expressed in decimal degrees.

label: Has Datetime Value
definition: A data property that has as its value a datetime value.

label: Has Uri Value
definition: A data property that has as its range a URI value.

label: Has Decimal Value
definition: A data property that has as its range a decimal value.

label: Has Double Value
definition: A data property that has as its range a double value.

label: Has Date Value
definition: A data property that has as its range a date value.

label: Has Boolean Value
definition: A data property that has as its range a boolean value.

label: Has Integer Value
definition: A data property that has as its range an integer value.

label: Entity
definition: (Elucidation) An entity is anything that exists or has existed or will exist

label: Continuant
definition: (Elucidation) A continuant is an entity that persists, endures, or continues to exist through time while maintaining its identity

label: Occurrent
definition: (Elucidation) An occurrent is an entity that unfolds itself in time or it is the start or end of such an entity or it is a temporal or spatiotemporal region

label: Independent Continuant
definition: b is an independent continuant =Def b is a continuant & there is no c such that b specifically depends on c or b generically depends on c

label: Spatial Region
definition: (Elucidation) A spatial region is a continuant entity that is a continuant part of the spatial projection of a portion of spacetime at a given time

label: Temporal Region
definition: (Elucidation) A temporal region is an occurrent over which processes can unfold

label: Two-dimensional Spatial Region
definition: (Elucidation) A two-dimensional spatial region is a spatial region that is a whole consisting of a surface together with zero or more surfaces which may have spatial regions of lower dimension as parts

label: Spatiotemporal Region
definition: (Elucidation) A spatiotemporal region is an occurrent that is an occurrent part of spacetime

label: Process
definition: (Elucidation) p is a process means p is an occurrent that has some temporal proper part and for some time t, p has some material entity as participant

label: Disposition
definition: (Elucidation) A disposition b is a realizable entity such that if b ceases to exist then its bearer is physically changed & b's realization occurs when and because this bearer is in some special physical circumstances & this realization occurs in virtue of the bearer's physical make-up

label: Realizable Entity
definition: (Elucidation) A realizable entity is a specifically dependent continuant that inheres in some independent continuant which is not a spatial region & which is of a type some instances of which are realized in processes of a correlated type

label: Zero-dimensional Spatial Region
definition: (Elucidation) A zero-dimensional spatial region is one or a collection of more than one spatially disjoint points in space

label: Quality
definition: (Elucidation) A quality is a specifically dependent continuant that, in contrast to roles and dispositions, does not require any further process in order to be realized

label: Specifically Dependent Continuant
definition: b is a specifically dependent continuant =Def b is a continuant & there is some independent continuant c which is not a spatial region & which is such that b specifically depends on c

label: Role
definition: (Elucidation) A role b is a realizable entity such that b exists because there is some single bearer that is in some special physical, social, or institutional set of circumstances in which this bearer does not have to be & b is not such that, if it ceases to exist, then the physical make-up of the bearer is thereby changed

label: Fiat Object Part
definition: (Elucidation) A fiat object part b is a material entity & such that if b exists then it is continuant part of some object c & demarcated from the remainder of c by one or more fiat surfaces

label: One-dimensional Spatial Region
definition: (Elucidation) A one-dimensional spatial region is a whole consisting of a line together with zero or more lines which may have points as parts

label: Object Aggregate
definition: (Elucidation) An object aggregate is a material entity consisting exactly of a plurality (≥1) of objects as member parts which together form a unit

label: Three-dimensional Spatial Region
definition: (Elucidation) A three-dimensional spatial region is a whole consisting of a spatial volume together with zero or more spatial volumes which may have spatial regions of lower dimension as parts

label: Site
definition: (Elucidation) A site is a three-dimensional immaterial entity whose boundaries either (partially or wholly) coincide with the boundaries of one or more material entities or have locations determined in relation to some material entity

label: Object
definition: (Elucidation) An object is a material entity which manifests causal unity & is of a type instances of which are maximal relative to the sort of causal unity manifested

label: Generically Dependent Continuant
definition: (Elucidation) A generically dependent continuant is an entity that exists in virtue of the fact that there is at least one of what may be multiple copies which is the content or the pattern that multiple copies would share

label: Function
definition: (Elucidation) A function is a disposition that exists in virtue of its bearer's physical make-up & this physical make-up is something the bearer possesses because it came into being either through evolution (in the case of natural biological entities) or through intentional design (in the case of artefacts) in order to realize processes of a certain sort

label: Process Boundary
definition: p is a process boundary =Def p is a temporal part of a process & p has no proper temporal parts

label: One-dimensional Temporal Region
definition: (Elucidation) A one-dimensional temporal region is a temporal region that is a whole that has a temporal interval and zero or more temporal intervals and temporal instants as parts

label: Material Entity
definition: (Elucidation) A material entity is an independent continuant has some portion of matter as continuant part

label: Continuant Fiat Boundary
definition: (Elucidation) A continuant fiat boundary b is an immaterial entity that is of zero, one or two dimensions & such that there is no time t when b has a spatial region as continuant part & whose location is determined in relation to some material entity

label: Immaterial Entity
definition: b is an immaterial entity =Def b is an independent continuant which is such that there is no time t when it has a material entity as continuant part

label: Fiat Line
definition: (Elucidation) A fiat line is a one-dimensional continuant fiat boundary that is continuous

label: Process Profile
definition: An occurrent that is an occurrent part of some process by virtue of the rate, or pattern, or amplitude of change in an attribute of one or more participants of said process.

label: Relational Quality
definition: b is a relational quality =Def b is a quality & there exists c and d such that c and d are not identical & b specifically depends on c & b specifically depends on d

label: Fiat Surface
definition: (Elucidation) A fiat surface is a two-dimensional continuant fiat boundary that is self-connected

label: Fiat Point
definition: (Elucidation) A fiat point is a zero-dimensional continuant fiat boundary that consists of a single point

label: Zero-dimensional Temporal Region
definition: (Elucidation) A zero-dimensional temporal region is a temporal region that is a whole consisting of one or more separated temporal instants as parts

label: History
definition: (Elucidation) A history is a process that is the sum of the totality of processes taking place in the spatiotemporal region occupied by the material part of a material entity

label: Temporal Interval
definition: (Elucidation) A temporal interval is a one-dimensional temporal region that is continuous, thus without gaps or breaks

label: Temporal Instant
definition: (Elucidation) A temporal instant is a zero-dimensional temporal region that has no proper temporal part

label: Deflecting Prism
definition: A Prism designed to deflect a beam of light entering the Prism by a fixed angle.

label: Cooling Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized in a process in which the thermal energy of a system decreases.

label: Designative Name
definition: A Designative Information Content Entity that consists of a string of characters that designates an entity within a specified cultural or social namespace and which is typically a word or phrase in a natural language that has an accepted cultural or social significance.

label: Change
definition: A Process in which some independent continuant endures and 1) one or more of the dependent entities it bears increase or decrease in intensity, 2) the entity begins to bear some dependent entity or 3) the entity ceases to bear some dependent entity.

label: Act
definition: A Process in which at least one Agent plays a causative role.

label: Upper Midrange Frequency
definition: A Sonic Frequency that is between 2 and 4 kHz.

label: Natural Process
definition: A Process existing in or produced by nature; rather than by the intent of human beings.

label: Sound Frequency
definition: A Frequency that is the rate of Oscillations per second of a Sound Wave.

label: Mass Density
definition: A Quality that inheres in a bearer in virtue of that bearer's mass per unit volume.

label: Incorporated Organization
definition: An Organization formed by an Act of Incorporation that consists of an association of individuals, created by law or under authority of law, having a continuous existence independent of the existences of its members and owners, and having powers and liabilities distinct from those of its members and owners.

label: Nominal Stasis
definition: A Stasis of Specifically Dependent Continuant in which some Independent Continuant bears a Quality or Realizable Entity that has a level of intensity or functionality that falls within the designed, expected, or acceptable range such that the Independent Continuant is of normal value, usefulness, or functionality.

label: Propulsion Control System
definition: A Control System that consists of control devices, displays, indicators, or modules designed to control a Propulsion System.

label: Gain Of Generically Dependent Continuant
definition: A Gain of Dependent Continuant wherein some Independent Continuant becomes the carrier of some Generically Dependent Continuant.

label: Aztec Code
definition: A Two-Dimensional Barcode that is used by the transportation industry to scan tickets.

label: Shotgun
definition: A Long Gun that fires packets of shot, a single slug, a sabot, or a specialty round (such as tear gas, bolo shell, or a breaching round) over shorter ranges than that of Rifles and with less accuracy.

label: Triangular Waveform
definition: A Waveform that is characterized by a triangular shape due to the continuous linear zig-zag transitions between minimum and maximum Amplitudes of the Wave Cycle.

label: Minor Axis
definition: A One-Dimensional Spatial Region that is the longest line segment perpendicular to the Major Axis that connects two points on the edge of an Ellipse.

label: Title Document
definition: A Legal Instrument that is designed as evidence of ownership.

label: Power Inverting Artifact Function
definition: A Current Conversion Artifact Function that is realized by processes in which some Artifact is used to convert direct current (DC) to alternating current (AC).

label: Container
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to contain (wholly or partially) some material entity.

label: Sensor Platform
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to support, and in some cases transport, a Sensor during its deployment and functioning.

label: Radio Communication Reception Artifact Function
definition: A Communication Reception Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact receives information transmitted from another Artifact, where the transmission of information occurs using radio waves.

label: Sensor Deployment Artifact Function

label: Act Of Advising
definition: An Act of Directive Communication performed by providing advice or counsel to another agent.

label: Electronic Stock
definition: Stock that consists of Bytes.

label: Hair Color
definition: A Quality inhering in a portion of Hair by virtue of its color.

label: Mailing

label: Dispersive Prism
definition: A Prism designed to break up a beam of light entering the Prism into its constituent spectral colors by leveraging the refractive index of light based on its Frequency.

label: Median Point Estimate Information Content Entity
definition: A Point Estimate Information Content Entity that is a measurement of a set of values and is equal to either the middle value or the average of the two values which separate the set into two equally populated upper and lower sets.

label: Nuclear Reactor
definition: A Power Source that is designed to initiate and control a self-sustained nuclear chain reaction to produce power in the form of heat, which can be transferred to a working fluid for further conversion to mechanical or electrical energy.

label: Atmospheric Feature
definition: A Geographic Feature that is part of the atmosphere (including the atmosphere itself as a non-proper part) having a relatively stable lifecycle and which has a location that can be distinguished from the surrounding portion of the atmosphere.

label: Church
definition: A Religious Facility that is designed for Christian worship and prayer.

label: Decrease Of Role
definition: A Decrease of Realizable Entity in which some Independent Continuant has a decrease of some Role that it bears.

label: Conveyance Artifact Function
definition: A Motion Artifact Function that is realized in a process in which the bearer of the function conveys entities from one location to another.

label: Soft X-ray Frequency
definition: An X-Ray Frequency that is between 30 petahertz and 3 exahertz.

label: Waste Management Artifact Function
definition: A Service Artifact Function that is realized in processes of collecting transporting processing recycling or disposing and monitoring of waste materials.

label: Act Of Observation
definition: A Planned Act of acquiring information from a source via the use of one or more senses.

label: System Role
definition: A Role that inheres in an entity in virtue of its parts or elements being arranged in such a way that they together exhibit behavior or meaning that they do not exhibit individually.

label: Portion Of Solid Fuel
definition: A Portion of Fuel that is stored in a solid state.

label: Grocery Store
definition: A Commercial Facility that is designed to sell food.

label: Hostel
definition: A Residential Facility that is designed to temporarily lodge guests in a sociable environment for relatively low costs.

label: Semicircular
definition: A Shape quality inhering in a bearer in virtue of the bearer having the shape of half a circle.

label: Portion Of Solid Propellant
definition: A Portion of Propellant that is stored in a solid state.

label: Eye Color
definition: A Quality inhering in an Eye by virtue of the color of the Eye's Iris.

label: Petroleum Depot
definition: A Storage Facility that is designed to store petroleum, oil, or lubricants.

label: Province

label: Flow Control Valve
definition: A Valve that is designed to regulate the flow or Pressure of a fluid.

label: Random Wire Antenna
definition: A Wire Antenna that consists of a long wire suspended above the ground with a length that does not bear a relation to the wavelength of the radio waves used and which is typically used as a receiving antenna on the long, medium, and short wave bands.

label: Banknote
definition: A Portion of Cash that consists of a portable slips of paper or fabric designed to bear some specified Financial Value.

label: Very High Frequency Communication Instrument
definition: A Radio Communication Instrument that is designed to participate in some process that has process part some Very High Frequency.

label: Act Of Construction
definition: An Act of Artifact Processing wherein Artifacts are built on site as prescribed by some contract.

label: Religious Facility
definition: A Facility that is designed for worship and prayer.

label: Ground Motor Vehicle
definition: A Ground Vehicle that is designed to receive its motive power from an Engine and is not designed to travel on rails.

label: Stirling Engine
definition: An External Combusion Engine that is designed to compress and expand some working fluid at different temperatures, such that there is a net conversion of heat energy to mechanical work.

label: Healthcare Facility
definition: A Facility that is designed for the diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of disease.

label: Reaction Engine
definition: An Engine that provides propulsion by expelling Reaction Mass.

label: Mobile Telephone
definition: A Telephone that is connected to a Telephone Network by radio waves.

label: Scalp Hair
definition: A Bodily Component that consists of a portion of hair that grows on the scalp of a human or other animal.

label: Telephone Line
definition: A Telecommunication Network Line that consists of a physical wire or other signaling medium that is designed to be part of a Telephone Network.

label: Open Pit Mine
definition: A Mine that is designed to support the extraction of materials from the ground directly without using tunnels.

label: Measurement Unit Of Flow
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of the rate at which portions of a substance pass per unit of time.

label: Frequency Measurement Artifact Function
definition: A Measurement Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to measure the Frequency of a specified object or class of objects.

label: Multi-hour Temporal Interval
definition: A one-dimensional temporal region that is measured in Hours and spans at least one Hour.

label: Book
definition: An Information Bearing Artifact that is designed to bear some specific Information Content Entity by means of ink, paper, parchment, or other materials fastened together to hinge at one side.

label: Act Of Location Change
definition: An Act of Motion in which the location of some Object is changed by some Agent.

label: Military Artifact Function
definition: A Service Artifact Function that is realized in processes related to the armed services.

label: Civil Time Reference System
definition: A Temporal Reference System that is a statutory time scale as designated by civilian authorities to determine local time(s).

label: Three-dimensional Path

label: Transcript

label: Ground Track Point
definition: A Zero-Dimensional Spatial Region that is an idealized point located on the surface of an Astronomical Body directly below an Object Track Point.

label: Town
definition: A Local Administrative Region in which a human population permanently resides that is typically larger than the population of a Village but smaller than that of a City; is designated as a town based on a particular administrative, legal, or historical status; and which delimits a local Government that typically exercises less power than that of a City Government.

label: Low Density Residential Area
definition: A Populated Place where houses are on lots of more than one acre.

label: Temporal Interval Identifier
definition: A Temporal Region Identifier that designates some Temporal Interval.

label: Measurement Unit Of Acceleration
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of the rate at which objects change their velocities per unit of time.

label: Optical Microscope
definition: A Microscope that is designed to use visible light and a system of Optical Lenses to produce a significantly enlarged image of the Object.

label: Wired Communication Artifact Function
definition: A Communication Artifact Function that is realized in a process that conveys meaningful signs by means of a (usually cylindrical) flexible strand or rod of metal.

label: Code Identifier
definition: A Non-Name Identifier that consists of a string of characters that was created and assigned according to an encoding system such that metadata can be derived from the identifier.

label: Act Of Estimation

label: Act Of Social Movement

label: Standard Time Of Day Identifier

label: Cutting Weapon

label: Green

label: Process Ending

label: Bodily Component

label: Minute

label: Ordinal Date Identifier

label: Firearm

label: Skill

label: Infrared Telescope

label: Portion Of Coolant

label: Bidirectional Transducer

label: Preferred Stock

label: Control Surface

label: Propulsion System

label: Complex Optical Lens

label: Electrical Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to perform a process involving electrical power.

label: Wave Process

label: Portion Of Liquid Oxygen

label: Skin Type

label: Vehicle Compartment

label: Underwater Mine

label: Square

label: Increase Of Generically Dependent Continuant

label: Rail Facility

label: Act Of Military Force

label: Mechanical Process

label: Air Inlet

label: Translucent

label: Ventilation Control Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized in processes in which some Artifact is used to control the quality of air in some space.

label: Unix Temporal Instant
definition: A Temporal Instant as specified by the number of Seconds that have elapsed since the specified Epoch Time as described by an implementation of Unix Time.

label: Stasis Of Disposition
definition: A Stasis of Realizable Entity in which some Independent Continuant bears some Disposition that remains unchanged during a Temporal Interval.

label: Pump
definition: A Fluid Control Artifact that is designed to impart motion to a portion of fluid to transport it within a system through the use of mechanical action.

label: Information Processing Artifact
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to use algorithms to transform some Information Content Entity into another Information Content Entity.

label: Artifact Function Specification
definition: A Directive Information Content Entity that prescribes some Artifact Function and which is part of some Artifact Model.

label: Spatial Orientation
definition: A Relational Quality that is the angle of Rotation of an Object relative to one or more Plane of Reference or Axis of Rotation.

label: Measurement Unit
definition: A Descriptive Information Content Entity that describes a definite magnitude of a physical quantity, defined and adopted by convention and/or by law, that is used as a standard for measurement of the same physical quantity.

label: Act Of Conducting Mass Media Interview
definition: An Act of Mass Media Communication involving a conversation between a reporter and a person of public interest, used as a basis of a broadcast or publication.

label: Vehicle Track Point
definition: An Object Track Point that is where a Vehicle is or was located during some motion.

label: Act Of Expressive Communication
definition: An Act of Communication in which an Agent expresses their attitudes or emotions towards some entity.

label: Solar Time Reference System
definition: A Temporal Reference System that is based on the position of the Sun in the sky.

label: Bounding Box Point
definition: A Geospatial Position that is a proper part of some Geospatial Region Bounding Box.

label: First-order Administrative Region
definition: A Government Domain that is a primary administrative division of a Country.

label: Performance Specification
definition: A Directive Information Content Entity that prescribes some aspect of the behavior of a participant in a Process given one or more operating conditions.

label: Portion Of Liquid Hydrogen
definition: A Portion of Cryogenic Material that is composed (almost) entirely of liquid hydrogen.

label: Tattoo
definition: A Bodily Component that consists of a typically permanent mark or design on a portion of skin that is created by a process of pricking and ingraining an indelible pigment or by raising scars.

label: Power Transformer

label: Increase Of Quality
definition: An Increase of Specifically Dependent Continuant in which some Indpendent Continuant has an increase of some Quality that it bears.

label: Recording Device

label: Act Of Directive Communication

label: Third-order Administrative Region

label: Stasis Of Specifically Dependent Continuant

label: Optical Instrument

label: Act Of Financial Deposit

label: Maximum Power

label: Domain Of A Country

label: Measurement Unit Of Amount Of Substance

label: Populace

label: Act Of Government

label: Cargo Cabin

label: Act Of Meeting

label: Incendiary Weapon

label: Artificial Language

label: Flight Transponder

label: Clockwise Rotational Motion
definition: A Rotational Motion in which the direction of rotation is toward the right as seen relative to the designated side of the plane of rotation.

label: Instant Messaging
definition: An Act of Communication by Media in which real-time direct text-based communication occurs between two or more people using personal computers or other devices, along with shared Instant Messaging Client Software conveyed over a network, such as the Internet.

label: Radio Frequency

label: Act Of Reporting

label: Telephone Network

label: Generator Control Unit

label: Mode Point Estimate Information Content Entity

label: Near Infrared Light Frequency

label: Hand Gun

label: Facial Hair

label: Lithium-ion Electric Battery

label: Timekeeping Instrument

label: Manual Tool

label: Z-axis

label: Criminal Act

label: Wave Cycle

label: Large-scale Rocket Launcher

label: Act Of Interpersonal Relationship

label: Very High Frequency

label: Object Track Point

label: Detergent Artifact Function

label: Base Of Operations

label: Civilian Role

label: Ultraviolet Telescope

label: Thrust

label: Hotel

label: Language Skill

label: Act Of Thanking

label: Fragrance Artifact Function

label: Axial Rotation Period
definition: A Temporal Interval that is equal to the length of time required for a spinning Object to complete one rotation around its Axis of Rotation.

label: Blunt

label: Artifact Version Ordinality

label: Certificate

label: Minimum Speed Artifact Function

label: Act Of Homicide

label: Facility

label: Telephone Subscriber Line

label: Electrical Contact Artifact Function

label: Heliport

label: Purple
definition: A Color that is aproximately midway between Red and Blue.

label: Process Beginning

label: Measurement Unit Of Sound Level

label: Camera

label: Act Of Pilgrimage

label: Act Of Change Of Residence

label: Event Status Nominal Information Content Entity

label: Rifle

label: Object Track

label: Friction Reduction Artifact Function

label: One-dimensional Geospatial Boundary

label: Act Of Congratulating

label: Sound Wavelength

label: Engine

label: Multi-day Temporal Interval
definition: A one-dimensional temporal region that is measured in Days and spans at least one Day.

label: Chemical Weapon

label: Subcontinent
definition: A Geospatial Region that is bounded by a large, relatively self-contained landmass forming a subdivision of a Continent.

label: Ammunition Depot
