definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of the rate of change of angular momentum of an object.

label: Effect
definition: A Process that follows and is caused by some previous Process.

label: Government Artifact Function
definition: A Service Artifact Function that is realized in processes in which public policy is administered and the actions of its members are directed.

label: Material Territory Of A Government Domain
definition: The portions of lithosphere, hydrosphere, or atmosphere that together exactly occupy a Government Domain

label: Power Transmission Artifact
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to transfer and regulate Power flow from a Power Source to an application point.

label: Radio Relay Station
definition: A Communications Facility that is designed to support the receiving and re-transmitting of radio signals.

label: Cleaning Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized in processes in which some Artifact is used to remove foreign objects from another object.

label: Neutral Person
definition: A Person who is the bearer of some Neutral Role.

label: Combat Outpost
definition: A Military Facility that is designed to support the conduction of combat operations of limited scope or size.

label: Battery Terminal
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to connect a load or charger to a single or multiple-cell Battery.

label: Distance Measurement Information Content Entity
definition: A Ratio Measurement Information Content Entity that is a measurement of a One-Dimensional Extent inhering in some Site that is externally connected to two Independent Continuants.

label: Distribution Port
definition: A Port that is designed with the cargo handling equipment necessary for the loading and unloading of Watercraft

label: Anti-bacterial Artifact Function
definition: An Anti-Microbial Artifact Function that is realized in a process which causes harm to, or the death of, some bacterium.

label: Super Low Frequency
definition: A Radio Frequency that is between 30 and 300 Hz.

label: Prosthetic Foot
definition: A Prosthesis that is designed to replace a missing foot.

label: Calendar Year
definition: A Year that begins and ends concurrently with the Days specified by a Calendar System to be the first and last Days of the Year.

label: Sound Wave Process
definition: A Mechanical Wave Process of Pressure and displacement that is parallel to the propogation direction of the Wave Process through a medium.

label: Act Of Inhabitancy
definition: A Planned Act in which a Person lives at a Site for a period of time that may be as short as 1 day/night or as long as the Person's entire life.

label: Product Transport Facility
definition: A Facility that is designed to transport some product.

label: Voltage Regulating Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized by processes in which some Artifact is used to cause a change in the voltage magnitude between the sending and receiving end of an electrical component.

label: Attitude Control Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized by an Artifact participating in an attitude control process.

label: Medical Depot
definition: A Storage Facility that is designed to store medical supplies.

label: External Navigation Lighting System
definition: A Lighting System that is designed to be attached to some Vehicle and to emit colored light in order to signal that Vehicle's position, heading, and status.

label: Mirror
definition: An Optical Instrument that is designed to reflect light that has a wavelength within a given range and is incident on its relflecting surface such that the reflected light maintains most of the characteristics of the original light.

label: Diminutive Name
definition: An Abbreviated Name that is a familiar form of a Proper Name.

label: Act Of Contract Formation
definition: An Act of Promising having a lawful object entered into voluntarily by two or more agents with legal capacity, each of whom intends to create one or more legal obligations between them.

label: Government Domain Border
definition: A Geospatial Boundary that is a boundary of some Government Domain.

label: Designative Information Content Entity
definition: An Information Content Entity that consists of a set of symbols that denote some Entity.

label: Act Of Training Acquisition
definition: An Act of Training performed by an Agent by acquiring knowledge from another Agent.

label: Turbofan Air-breathing Jet Engine
definition: An Air-Breathing Jet Engine that uses a Turbofan, which consists of a Turbine and a Fan.

label: Switch Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized in a process of breaking an electric circuit by interrupting the current or diverting it from one conductor to another.

label: Telecommunication Instrument
definition: A Communication Instrument that is designed for use by some Agent in some Act of Communication where the recipient of that communication is potentially a significant distance away from the Agent.

label: Fuel Tank
definition: A Container that is designed to store a Portion of Fuel.

label: Probability Measurement Information Content Entity
definition: A Measurement Information Content Entity that is a measurement of the likelihood that a Process or Process Aggregate occurs.

label: Mass Specification
definition: A Quality Specification that prescribes the Amount of Mass that a Material Entity should have.

label: Nozzle Mouth
definition: A Fluid Control Artifact that consists of the portion of a Nozzle at the end that is designed to be where the flow of fluid exits the Nozzle.

label: Radiolucent
definition: A Radiopacity that inheres in a bearer in virtue of its capacity to permit most X-rays to pass through it.

label: Ideology
definition: An Information Content Entity that consists of a collection of claims about how some part of the world is or should be and which is accepted as true by an Agent or Group of Agents such that it forms the basis of their beliefs, goals, expectations, and motivations.

label: Enemy Person
definition: A Person who is the bearer of some Enemy Role.

label: Convergent-divergent Nozzle
definition: A Nozzle that consists of a tube with an asymmetric hourglass shape that is designed to accelerate hot pressurized gas by converting the heat energy of the gas flow into kinetic energy as it passes through the Nozzle Throat to generate increased Exhaust Velocity of the gas as it exits the Nozzle.

label: Afternoon
definition: A Temporal Interval that consists of the temporal regions between when the sun is at its apex (approximately 12:00pm) and when it sets (approximately 6:00pm).

label: Computer Network
definition: A Telecommunication Network that is designed to allow the exchange of data between two or more computers connected to the network.

label: Wire Receiver
definition: A Radio Receiver that uses a Wire Antenna to intercept radio signals.

label: Image
definition: An Information Bearing Artifact that is designed to carry an Information Content Entity that represents some entity owing to a visual isomorphism between the carrying artifact and the entity.

label: System Clock
definition: A Timekeeping Instrument that is part of a computer an is designed to issue a steady high-frequency signal that is used to synchronize all of the computer's internal components.

label: Tunnel
definition: A Land Transportation Artifact that is designed to enable Ground Vehicles to travel underneath a surrounding soil, earth, or rock formation.

label: Power Transmission Line
definition: A Product Transport Facility that is designed to transmit electricity over distance via a system of above ground wires including their supports.

label: Terminal Board
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to join electrical terminations and create an electrical circuit by means of a block which connects individual wires without a splice or physically joining the ends.

label: Measurement Unit Of Angle
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of the angle between two lines or planes in relation to a vertex.

label: Water Tower
definition: A Facility that is the bearer of functions realized in processes of storing water in an elevated container.

label: Visual Prosthesis
definition: An Artificial Eye that is designed to replace a missing eye, which performs the function of an eye.

label: Command Post Facility
definition: A Military Facility that is designed to support the command and control of Military Operations or Forces.

label: Semi-automatic Pistol
definition: A Hand Gun that has a single fixed firing chamber machined into the rear of the barrel and an ammunition magazine capable of holding multiple Cartridges such that the Hand Gun is designed to automatically reload each time it is fired and to fire a Bullet with each successive pull of the trigger until the stored ammunition is depleted.

label: Acceleration
definition: A Process Profile that is the rate of change of the Velocity of an object.

label: Vehicle
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to facilitate the movement of material entities from one location to another by conveying them there.

label: Horn Antenna
definition: A Radio Antenna that consists of a flaring metal waveguide shaped like a horn to direct radio waves in a beam and can be used on its own or as a feeder for larger antenna structures, such as Parabolic Antennas.

label: Prosthesis
definition: A Medical Artifact that is designed to replace a missing body part.

label: Electric Battery
definition: An Electrical Power Source that is designed to produce electric power by converting chemical energy to electrical energy.

label: Fossil Fuel Power Plant
definition: An Electric Power Station that is designed to convert fossil fuels (e.g. coal, natural gas, or petroleum) into electrical energy.

label: Village
definition: A Local Administrative Region in which a human population permanently resides that is typically larger than the population of a hamlet but smaller than that of a Town.

label: Counterfeit Instrument
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to be a fake replica of some genuine Artifact.

label: Cryogenic Storage Dewar
definition: A Container that is designed to store a Portion of Cryogenic Material (such as liquid helium or liquid oxygen) and which consists of, minimally, walls that are constructed from two or more layers that are separated by a high vacuum to provide thermal insulation between the interior and exterior of the dewar.

label: Polarizing Prism
definition: A Prism designed to split a beam of light entering the Prism into components of varying polarization.

label: Sea Level
definition: A Fiat Surface that divides the spheroid composed of Earth and its atmosphere at some point that corresponds to the mean level of calm water in the Earth’s oceans.

label: Vehicle Control System
definition: A Control System that is designed to enable some Agent to control some Vehicle.

label: Parabolic Antenna
definition: A Radio Antenna that uses a parabolic reflector to direct or receive radio waves and has a very high gain.

label: Wedding
definition: An Act of Ceremony in which two Persons are united in Marriage or a similar institution.

label: Decrease Of Dependent Continuant
definition: A Change in which some Independent Continuant has a decrease in the level of some Dependent Continuant that it bears.

label: Communication Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized in a process in which meaningful signs are conveyed from one entity to another.

label: Submillimeter Wavelength Radio Telescope
definition: A Radio Telescope that is designed to aid in the observation of spatially distant Objects by means of collecting and focusing radio waves from the submillimeter waveband (i.e. microwaves) to form an enhanced image of the Object.

label: Spherical Coordinate System
definition: A Spatial Reference System for three-dimensional spatial regions that identifies each point using an ordered triple of numerical coordinates that consist of the radial distance of the point of interest from a fixed origin, its polar angle measured from a fixed zenith direction, and the azimuth angle of its orthogonal projection measured from a fixed direction on a reference plane that passes through the origin and is orthogonal to the zenith.

label: Hydraulic Power Transfer Unit
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to transfer hydraulic power from one of an Aircraft's hydraulic systems to another in the event that a system has failed or been turned off.

label: Deviation Measurement Information Content Entity
definition: A Measurement Information Content Entity that is a measurement of the extent to which an entity conforms to how it is expected or supposed to be.

label: Microwave Frequency
definition: A Radio Frequency that is between 300 MHz and 300 GHz.

label: Spherical
definition: A Three Dimensional Shape inhering in a bearer in virtue of all of its cross sections being round.

label: Land Mine
definition: An Explosive Weapon that is designed to be concealed under or on the ground and to detonate as its target passes over or near it.

label: Geospatial Region Bounding Box Identifier List
definition: A Measurement Unit of Geocoordinate that is comprised of 4 pairs of coordinates, one for each of the 4 defining points (North, West, South, East) of a Geospatial Region Bounding Box.

label: Transducer
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to convert one form of energy to another.

label: Forward Operations Base
definition: A Military Base that is located relatively close to an offensive Area of Operations, is supported by the Base of Operations, and is designed to support local strategic objectives and tactical operations.

label: Length
definition: A One Dimensional Extent that inheres in a bearer in virtue of the bearer's greatest extent in one direction.

label: Act Of Sojourn
definition: An Act of Inhabitancy in which a Person lives in a dwelling temporarily, often during stages of an Act of Travel.

label: Resource
definition: A Continuant that is owned by, in the possession of, or is otherwise controlled by an Agent such that it could be used by that Agent.

label: Act Of Targeting
definition: A Planned Act wherein some Agent maintains one or more entities as the objects of potential action given some operational requirement.

label: Ignition System
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to produce an Ignition process.

label: Chart
definition: An Image that is designed to carry some Representational Information Content Entity that is prescribed by some canonical visual format.

label: Act Of Social Group Membership
definition: An Act of Association wherein a Person belongs to some Social Group.

label: Point Estimate Information Content Entity
definition: An Estimate Information Content Entity that consists of a single value for the measured entity.

label: Combustion Engine
definition: A Heat Engine that is designed to convert thermal energy that is generated through a local Combustion process into mechanical energy.

label: Canal
definition: A Water Transportation Artifact that is an artificial Hydrographic Feature designed to convey water or enable Watercraft to travel inland.

label: Bullet
definition: A Portion of Ammunition that is designed to be projected by a Firearm, Sling, Slingshot, or Air Gun, but which does not (typically) contain explosives.

label: Julian Day Number
definition: A Decimal Date Identifier that designates some Julian Day by using a number to indicate the sequential ordering of the Day since the Julian Date epoch.

label: Text Messaging
definition: An Act of Communication by Media involving the exchange of brief written messages between fixed-line phone or mobile phone and fixed or portable devices over a network.

label: Action Permission
definition: A Process Regulation that permits some Process.

label: Wave Process Profile
definition: A Process Profile of a Wave Process.

label: Ultra Low Frequency
definition: A Radio Frequency that is between 300 Hz and 3 kHz.

label: Electromagnetic Radiation Frequency
definition: A Frequency that is characterized by the rate of Oscillations per second of an Electromagnetic Wave.

label: Zenith
definition: A One-Dimensional Spatial Region that extends from a given location upward along the local vertical direction pointing in the direction opposite the apparent Gravitational Force at that location.

label: Database
definition: An Information Bearing Artifact that is designed to bear some set of specific Information Content Entities and to be rapidly searchable and retrievable.

label: Synagogue
definition: A Religious Facility that is designed for Judaic worship and prayer.

label: Component Role
definition: A Role that inheres in an entity having a discrete structure in virtue of that entity being part of a system considered at a particular level of analysis.

label: Color Saturation
definition: An Optical Property that inheres in a bearer in virtue of its capacity to reflect high intensity light distributed across fewer wavelengths, typically considered on a continuum of purity.

label: Surface Wave Profile
definition: A Wave Process Profile in which the Wave Process propogates along the surface of a medium and which involves both transverse and longitudinal wave profiles such that the motion of the displacement of participating particles is circular or elliptical.

label: Pier
definition: A Transportation Facility that is designed to partially enclose a harbor and form a landing place for Watercraft.

label: Fungicide Artifact Function
definition: An Anti-Microbial Artifact Function that is realized in a process which causes harm to, or the death of, some fungus or fungal spore.

label: Velocity
definition: A Process Profile of an object's Motion that is characterized by its Speed and direction with respect to a frame of reference.

label: Optical Focusing Artifact Function
definition: An Optical Processing Artifact Function that is realized by an Artifact participating in a light focusing event in which the Artifact causes the light beam to converge on a target spatial point.

label: Wave Production
definition: A Natural Process in which a Wave Process is generated.

label: Hardness
definition: A Quality that inheres in a bearer in virtue of the degree to which it can be turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

label: Lubrication System
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to contain, transfer, and regulate the flow of lubricant to multiple locations in an Artifact.

label: Amount
definition: A Quality that inheres in a bearer in virtue of the total, aggregate or sum of a number of discrete items or material the entity contains as parts.

label: Act Of Requesting
definition: An Act of Directive Communication performed by asking for something.

label: Measurement Unit Of Density
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of the mass of an object per unit of its total volume.

label: Imaging Instrument
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to produce images (visual representations) of an entity.

label: Impulsive Force
definition: A Process Profile that is the integral of a Force that is applied to a portion of matter over a period of time.

label: Curvilinear Motion
definition: A Translational Motion process in which an Object moves along a curved path.

label: Video Camera
definition: A Camera that is designed to form and digitally or physically record a continuous stream of subsequent images of an entity or scene such that the images can be played back in succession as a video.

label: Locomotive
definition: A Rail Transport Vehicle that is designed to provide the motive power for a Train.

label: Signal Detection Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized in the process of discerning between information-bearing patterns and random patterns, or noise, that distract from the information.

label: Hydraulic Motor
definition: A Physically Powered Engine that converts hydraulic pressure and flow into torque and angular displacement.

label: Chemical Depot
definition: A Storage Facility that is designed to store chemicals.

label: Portion Of Cryosphere
definition: A fiat object part of the frozen part of a natural satellite's hydosphere

label: Ethnicity
definition: A Quality that inheres in its bearers by virtue of a common heritage, often consisting of a common language, a common culture (often including a shared religion) and an ideology that stresses common ancestry or endogamy.

label: Control System
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to manage, command, direct, or regulate the behavior of at least one other Artifact.

label: Factory
definition: A Facility that is designed for manufacturing or refining material products.

label: Stasis Of Non-mission Capable Maintenance
definition: A Stasis of Non-Mission Capable during which the participating Continuant is not capable of performing its primary functions for the specified Mission due to participating in an Act Of Maintenance.

label: Optical Property
definition: An Electromagnetic Radiation Property that is realized when its bearer interacts with electromagnetic waves within the visible light spectrum.

label: Radio Repeater
definition: A Radio Transceiver that is designed to receive a radio signal, amplify it, and retransmit it (often on another frequency).

label: Increase Of Role
definition: An Increase of Realizable Entity in which some Independent Continuant has an increase of some Role that it bears.

label: Altitude
definition: A Height that inheres in a Site that externally connects an Independent Continuant to either the surface of the Earth or the Earth's mean Sea Level.

label: Turbine Steam Engine
definition: A Steam Engine that is designed to extract thermal energy from pressurized steam and use it to do mechanical work on a rotating output shaft.

label: Translational Motion
definition: A Motion Process in which the participating Object changes its position from one portion of space to another.

label: Direct Current Power Source
definition: An Electrical Power Source that is designed to transfer electrical power in the form of direct current.

label: Chemical Reaction Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized in a process that leads to the transformation of one set of chemical substances to another.

label: Catadioptric Optical Telescope
definition: An Optical Telescope that is designed to aid in the observation of spatially distant Objects by means of collecting and focusing visible light through the use of a combination of Lenses and Mirrors to form an enhanced image of the Object.

label: Fuel Ventilation System
definition: A Fluid Control Artifact that is designed to allow air into the Fuel Tank to take the place of burned fuel.

label: Geospatial Ellipse
definition: A One-Dimensional Geospatial Boundary that is formed by following a symmetric arc between four vertices which are connected to the center point of the ellipse via a straight line.

label: Electrical Conduction Artifact Function
definition: An Electrical Artifact Function that is realized by an Artifact being used to conduct an electric current.

label: Rail Transport Vehicle
definition: A Ground Vehicle that is designed to convey cargo, passengers, or equipment by Railway.

label: Hazel
definition: A Color that is a combination of Brown and Green, typically associated with eye color.

label: Information Bearing Artifact
definition: A Material Artifact that carries an Information Content Entity and is designed to do so using a particular format or structure.

label: List
definition: An Information Bearing Artifact that consists of one or more Information Bearing Artifacts that carry Information Content Entities and are the subjects of some Sequence Position Ordinality.

label: Day
definition: A Temporal Interval that is equal to the approximate length of time required for an Astronomical Body to complete one rotation around its Rotational Axis as specified relative to a particular Temporal Reference System.

label: Y-axis
definition: A Coordinate System Axis designated by the variable 'y'.

label: Stage
definition: An Entertainment Facility that is designed to provide a space upon which entertaining performances or productions can occur.

label: Round
definition: A Shape Quality that inheres in a bearer in virtue of every point along its circumference being equidistant from the center.

label: Prism
definition: An Optical Instrument that is designed to refract light and which consists of a transparent material with flat polished surfaces where at least two of these surfaces have an angle between them.

label: Coiled
definition: A Shape Quality inhering in a bearer in virtue of the bearer being wound in concentric rings or spirals.

label: Power Tool
definition: A Tool that is designed to be actuated by a Power Source and mechanism other than or in addition to manual labor.

label: Compression Ignition Engine
definition: An Internal Combustion Engine that is designed to operate by igniting a portion of Fuel and Oxidizer mixture using heat generated via compression of the mixture.

label: Reactant Artifact Function
definition: A Chemical Reaction Artifact Function that is realized in a process in which a substance or compound is added to a system in order to bring about a chemical reaction and is consumed in the course of the reaction.

label: Submersible Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized in processes of operating while submerged in water.

label: Multi-week Temporal Interval
definition: A one-dimensional temporal region that is measured in Weeks and spans at least one Week.

label: Radio Wave Conversion Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized by an Artifact being used to convert electric power into radio waves or radio waves into electric power.

label: Electromagnetic Pulse
definition: An Electromagnetic Wave Process that consists of a short high-energy burst of electromagnetic energy.

label: Portion Of Nuclear Fuel
definition: A Portion of Material that is designed to be used in a nuclear fission process to produce energy.

label: Water Treatment Facility
definition: A Facility that is designed for making water more acceptable for a specific end-use.

label: Folded
definition: A Shape Quality inhering in a bearer in virtue of one part of the bearer being layered over another connected part.

label: Portion Of Liquid Nitrogen
definition: A Portion of Cryogenic Material that is composed (almost) entirely of liquid nitrogen.

label: Geospatial Line String
definition: A One-Dimensional Geospatial Boundary that has two or more Geospatial Positions as vertices, where each vertex is connected to only one other vertex by a straight line.

label: Orange
definition: A Color that is between Red and Yellow with a wavelength in the visible spectrum typically between 590 to 635 nanometers.

label: Stasis
definition: A Process in which one or more Independent Continuants endure in an unchanging condition.

label: Stasis Of Function
definition: A Stasis of Realizable Entity in which some Independent Continuant bears some Function that remains unchanged during a Temporal Interval.

label: Act Of Promising
definition: An Act of Commissive Communication performed by declaring that the promising agent will do, or refrain from doing, the specified action.

label: Very Low Frequency
definition: A Radio Frequency that is between 3 and 30 kHz.

label: Optical Communication Artifact Function
definition: An Electromagnetic Communication Artifact Function that is realized in a process that conveys meaningful signs by means of visible light.

label: Stasis Of Role
definition: A Stasis of Realizable Entity in which some Independent Continuant bears some Role that remains unchanged during a Temporal Interval.

label: Telecommunication Network Line
definition: A Communication Artifact that is designed to be the physical transmission medium that connects two or more Telecommunication Network Nodes within a Telecommunication Network to facilitate communication between the Nodes.

label: Refractivity
definition: A Radiation Reflectivity that inheres in a bearer in virtue of the capacity of that bearer to change the direction of a propagating wave when passing through it.

label: Time Of Day Identifier
definition: A Temporal Instant Identifier that designates some Time of Day.

label: Pesticide Artifact Function
definition: A Poison Artifact Function that is realized in a process which causes illness in, or the death of, a living thing that is detrimental to humans or human concerns.

label: Time Zone Identifier
definition: A Spatial Region Identifier that designates the region associated with some uniform standard time for legal, commercial, or social purposes.

label: Speed
definition: A Process Profile that is characterized by the magnitude of an object's motion with respect to a frame of reference during some time period.

label: Herbicide Artifact Function
definition: A Pesticide Artifact Function that is realized in a process which causes harm to, or the death to, unwanted plants.

label: Year
definition: A Temporal Interval that is equal to the approximate length of time required for an Astronomical Body to complete one Orbital Revolution around its Primary Body as specified relative to a particular Temporal Reference System.

label: Julian Date Identifier
definition: A Decimal Time of Day Identifier that designates a Julian Date and is composed of both a Julian Day Number and a Julian Date Fraction.

label: Mid Infrared Light Frequency
definition: An Infrared Light Frequency that is between 20 and 214 terahertz.

label: Body Shape
definition: A Shape Quality inhering in a Person's body by virtue of the body's general outline or figure.

label: Act Of Financial Instrument Use
definition: An Act of Artifact Employment in which some Agent uses some Financial Instrument.

label: Family
definition: A Group of Persons related to one another by ancestry or marriage.

label: Portion Of Fuel
definition: A Portion of Material that is designed to release thermal energy when reacted with other substances.

label: Act Of Donating
definition: An Act of Financial Instrument Use wherein a Financial Instrument is tranfered by an Agent (the Donor) to another Agent (the Recipient) without return consideration.

label: Bicycle
definition: A Ground Vehicle that consists of two wheels, one in front of the other, attached to a frame along with handlebars and pedals such that it is designed to receive its motive power from pedaling.

label: Explosive Artifact Function
definition: A Damaging Artifact Function that is realized in a process in which the structural integrity of an entity is impaired beucase of the rapid increase in volume and release of energy in an extreme manner.

label: Sub-bass Frequency
definition: A Sonic Frequency that is between 20 and 60 Hz.

label: Solar Panel
definition: An Electrical Power Source that consists in part of one or more photovoltaic (i.e. solar) cells that convert light energy (photons) directly into electricity by means of the photovoltaic effect.

label: Measurement Unit Of Temperature
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of the thermal energy in an object.

label: Proportional Ratio Measurement Information Content Entity
definition: A Ratio Measurement Information Content Entity that is a measurement of a portion of a whole (described by the numerator) compared against that whole (described by the denominator) where the whole is a nominally described set of like entities.

label: Hydroelectric Power Plant
definition: An Electric Power Station that is designed to convert hydropower into electrical power.

label: Active Stasis
definition: A Stasis of Artifact Operationality that holds during a Temporal Interval when an Artifact is realizing one or more of its designed Artifact Functions (especially one of its primary functions).

label: Mounted Gun
definition: A Firearm that is designed to be fired while mounted.

label: Heating System
definition: An Environment Control System that is designed to heat the air or objects in a Site.

label: Stasis Of Quality
definition: A Stasis of Specifically Dependent Continuant in which some Independent Continuant bears some Quality that remains unchanged during a Temporal Interval.

label: Light Machine Gun
definition: A Long Gun that is designed to fire bullets in quick succession from an ammunition belt or magazine and to be employed by an individual soldier, with or without assistance, and typically weighing 9-22 lbs.

label: Measurement Unit Of Work
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of displacements of points to which Forces have been applied.

label: Descriptive Information Content Entity
definition: An Information Content Entity that consists of a set of propositions that describe some Entity.

label: Decrease Of Realizable Entity
definition: A Decrease of Specifically Dependent Continuant in which some Independent Continuant has a decrease of some Realizable Entity that it bears.

label: Effect Of Location Change
definition: An Effect caused by some Act of Location Change and which results in an Object being located in a different place.

label: Artifact History
definition: A History of an Artifact.

label: Ultra High Frequency Communication Instrument
definition: A Radio Communication Instrument that is designed to participate in some process that has process part some Ultra High Frequency.

label: Improvised Explosive Device
definition: An Explosive Weapon that is designed to be used in non-conventional military action.

label: Television Broadcast
definition: An Act of Communciation by Media that is transmitted to an audience through a television network.

label: Allied Person
definition: A Person who is the bearer of some Ally Role.

label: Split
definition: A Shape Quality inhering in a bearer in virtue of the bearer having a linear opening, or having been divided into parts.

label: Sound Process Profile
definition: A Process Profile that is part of a sound reception process and is characterized by properties of incoming sound waves as they are translated by some sensory system.

label: Act Of Confessing
definition: An Act of Representative Communication in which a person makes an admission of misdeeds or faults.

label: Public Safety Artifact Function
definition: A Service Artifact Function that is realized in processes of preventing and responding to events that could endanger the safety of the general public from significant danger, injury/harm, or damage, such as crimes or disasters (natural or man-made).

label: Loss Of Specifically Dependent Continuant
definition: A Loss of Dependent Continuant in which some Independent Continuant ceases to be the bearer of some Specifically Dependent Continuant.

label: Radio Broadcast
definition: An Act of Communciation by Media that is transmitted to an audience through a radio network.

label: Pipeline
definition: A Product Transport Facility that is designed to transport goods or materials through a pipe.

label: Rocket Pod
definition: A Rocket Launcher that is designed to contain several Unguided Rockets held in individual tubes and to be used by Aircraft or Helicopters for close air support.

label: Optical Camera
definition: A Camera that is designed to form and record an image generated from visible light.

label: Infrastructure System
definition: A Material Entity that is composed of elements bearing Infrastructure Roles and is by itself sufficient to provide a planned service or benefit to some organization that maintains its elements.

label: Plant
definition: An Organism that is multicellular, eukaryotic, autotrophic, and has cells that contain chloroplasts and walls made of cellulose.

label: Brown
definition: A Color that consists of dark orange and red, and of very low intensity.

label: Physiographic Feature
definition: A Geographic Feature that is a geomorphological unit characterized by its surface form and location in the landscape.

label: Video
definition: An Information Bearing Artifact that is designed to bear some specific Information Content Entity in the form of a sequence of representations that are presented sufficiently rapidly to create the appearance of motion and continuity.

label: Act Of Personal Communication
definition: An Act of Communication having a small audience.

label: Loss Of Dependent Continuant
definition: A Change in which some Independent Continuant ceases to be the bearer or carrier of some Dependent Continuant.

label: Brake Control System
definition: A Vehicle Control System that is designed to control the process of braking with the aim of preventing rolling, skidding, and hydroplaning.

label: Identification Friend Or Foe Transponder
definition: A Radio Transponder that is designed to automatically transmit a predefined signal in response to receiving an appropriate interrogation signal such that the entity it is located on can be positively identified as friendly.

label: Act Of Religious Group Affiliation
definition: An Act of Association wherein some Person belongs to some Religious Demonination or sub-Denomination.

label: Religious Artifact Function
definition: A Service Artifact Function that is realized in processes related to worship and prayer.

label: Storage Facility
definition: A Facility that is designed to store materials or goods.

label: Wind Farm
definition: An Electric Power Station that is designed to convert the wind's kinetic energy into electrical power by means of wind turbines.

label: Act Of Inviting
definition: An Act of Commissive Communication performed by requesting the presence or participation of the audience, and which may include offering an incentive or inducement.

label: Act Of Loaning
definition: An Act of Financial Instrument Use wherein a Financial Instrument is given by an Agent (the Creditor) to another Agent (the Debtor) in order to receive Repayments from the Debtor which are of greater Financial Value.

label: Wavy
definition: A Shape Quality inhering in a bearer in virtue of it having a sinuous or rippled border.

label: Wired Communication Reception Artifact Function
definition: A Communication Reception Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact receives information transmitted from another Artifact, where the transmission of information occurs via a direct connection using an electrical conductor.

label: City
definition: A Local Administrative Region in which a relatively large human population permanently resides; is designated as a city based on a particular administrative, legal, or historical status; and which delimits a local Government that typically oversees the provision of systems for sanitation, utilities, land usage, housing, and transportation.

label: High Frequency Communication Instrument
definition: A Radio Communication Instrument that is designed to participate in some process that has process part some High Frequency.

label: Visible Observation
definition: An Act of Observation that involves visual perception.

label: Act Of Travel
definition: An Act of Location Change wherein one or more Persons move between relatively distant geographical locations for any purpose and any duration, with or without any means of transport.

label: Calendar System
definition: A Temporal Reference System that is designed to organize and identify dates.

label: Depth
definition: A One Dimensional Extent that inheres in a bearer in virtue of the bearer's extension in a downward, backward, or inward direction.

label: Information Medium Artifact
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to have some Information Bearing Artifact as part.

label: Decimal Date Identifier
definition: A Date Identifier that designates some Day by using a number to indicate the sequential ordering of the Day since a specified Reference Time.

label: Married
definition: A Stasis of Generically Dependent Continuant that consists of a socially, culturally, or ritually recognized union or legal contract between spouses that establishes rights and obligations between them, between them and their children, and between them and their in-laws.

label: Mean Point Estimate Information Content Entity
definition: A Point Estimate Information Content Entity that is a measurement of a set of values and is equal to the sum of all the values in the set divided by the total number of values in the set.

label: Portion Of Oxidizer
definition: A Portion of Material that is disposed to steal electrons from other substances (i.e. to oxidize other substances) as a participant in a reduction-oxidation process.

label: Geopolitical Power Role
definition: A Role had by an Organization, that is perceived by an International Community as capable of performing influential acts in that community, and which would be realized in performing such acts.

label: Msi Plessey Barcode
definition: A One-Dimensional Barcode that consists of an indefinite number of numerical characters and is used for inventory control and marking storage containers and shelves in warehouse environments.

label: Radio Communication Relay Artifact Function
definition: A Communication Relay Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to first receive and then transmit information without the use of wires from one Artifact to another for the purpose of communiction.

label: Decontamination Facility
definition: A Washing Facility that is designed to wash personnel or equipment after (potential) contamination by radioactive, biological, or chemical material.

label: Act Of Facility Use
definition: An Act of Artifact Employment in which an Agent makes use of some Facility.

label: Radio Communication Instrument
definition: A Communication Instrument that is designed to enable communication between two or more entities via the use of radio waves.

label: Vehicle Track
definition: An Object Track for a Vehicle during some motion.

label: Post Office
definition: A Mailing Facility that is designed for serving customers of the national postal system.

label: Email Box
definition: A Telecommunication Instrument that is designed to be the delivery destination of Email Messages that are addressed to the corresponding Email Address.

label: Telephone
definition: A Telecommunication Instrument that is designed to provide point-to-point communication between agents by means of audio messages.

label: Act Of Artifact Processing
definition: A Planned Act of performing a series of mechanical or chemical operations on something in order to change or preserve it.

label: Emergency Ac/dc Power Source
definition: An Electrical Power Source that is designed to provide electrical power in an emergency situation by means of both alternating current and direct current.

label: Amplitude
definition: A Process Profile of an Oscillation Process that is the absolute value of the maximum displacement from a zero, equilibrium, or mean value during one cycle of the Oscillation Process.

label: Semi-major Axis
definition: A One-Dimensional Spatial Region that is equal to half the length of the Major Axis of an Ellipse.

label: Pyramidal
definition: A Three Dimensional Shape that inheres in a bearer in virtue of it having a polygonal base with vertices that all connect to the same apex to form triangular faces.

label: Maroon
definition: A Color consisting of purple and brown hue.

label: Group Of Persons
definition: A Group of Agents that has only Persons as parts.

label: Acronym
definition: An Abbreviated Name that combines the initial letters of a Designative Name and which is pronounced as a word.

label: Lunar Calendar System
definition: A Calendar System that is designed to organize and identify dates based on the cycles of the Moon's phases.

label: Permanent Resident Role
definition: A role inhering in a Person by virtue of that Person being recognized as having legal resident status in a Government Domain in which that person is not a citizen but where they have the right to reside on a permanent basis.

label: Telecommunication Network Node
definition: A Communication Artifact that consists of a connection point, redistribution point, or endpoint that is designed to be part of a Telecommunication Network and can be either active or passive.

label: Parts List
definition: A Quality Specification that prescribes the Amount of some type of Artifact that are part of or located on another Artifact.

label: Death
definition: A Natural Process in which all biological functions that sustain a living organism cease.

label: Calendar Day
definition: A Day that begins and ends concurrently with the Seconds specified by a Calendar System to be the first and last Seconds of the Day.

label: Act Of Arrival
definition: An Act of Location Change that consists of the participating entity reaching its destination such that the larger Act of Location Change is completed.

label: Arbitrary Identifier
definition: A Non-Name Identifier that consists of a string of characters that does not follow an encoding system.

label: Beginning Of Life Stasis
definition: A Operational Stasis that holds during a Temporal Interval when an Artifact is first put into operational use such that its designed set of Artifact Functions is capable of operating at or near their designed peak performance levels.

label: Act Of Military Training Acquisition
definition: An Act of Training Acquisition performed by an Agent by acquiring knowledge of the tactics, techniques, and/or strategies of Military Operations from an Agent or communication medium that realizes a capacity derived from its affiliation with a Military Organization.

label: Act Of Apologizing
definition: An Act of Expressive Communication performed by acknowledging and expressing regret for a fault, shortcoming, or failure.

label: Bass Frequency
definition: A Sonic Frequency that is between 60 and 250 Hz.

label: Train Car
definition: A Rail Transport Vehicle that consists of a single Vehicle that is not a Train but is designed to be connected to other Train Cars along with at least one Locomotive to form a Train.

label: Part Role
definition: A Role that inheres in an entity in virtue of it being part of some other entity without being subject to further subdivision or disassembly without destruction of its designated use.

label: Nickel-metal Hydride Electric Battery
definition: A Secondary Cell Electric Battery that has a metal-hydride anode and nickel oxide hydroxide cathode.

label: Upc-a Barcode
definition: A UPC Barcode that consists of 12 numerical digits.

label: Computing Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized by an Artifact participating in a computation process.

label: Landline Telephone
definition: A Telephone that is connected to a Telephone Network through a pair of wires.

label: Constituent State
definition: A First-Order Administrative Region that is part of a Country and delimits a centralized regional Government that holds constitutionally-defined administrative jurisdiction over the defined geographic territory that bounds the State.

label: Act Of Legal Instrument Use
definition: An Act of Artifact Employment in which some Agent uses some Legal Instrument.

label: Deactivated Stasis
definition: A Stasis of Artifact Operationality that holds during a Temporal Interval when an Artifact is not realizing any of its designed Artifact Functions (or at least not realizing any of its primary functions).

label: Inhibiting Motion Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized by processes in which some Artifact is used to inhibit the motion of some object.

label: Financial Artifact Function
definition: A Service Artifact Function that is realized in processes of managing money.

label: Geospatial Line
definition: A Geospatial Line String that has only two vertices.

label: Measurement Unit Of Momentum
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of the Momentum of a portion of matter that is in Motion.

label: Phosphorescence
definition: A Luminescent Property that inheres in a bearer in virtue of that bearer's capacity to emit visible light after absorbing shorter wavelength radiation, and to continue emitting after the absorbing process has ceased.

label: Sniper Rifle
definition: A Rifle that is designed to be highly accurate for long-range precision tactical shooting.

label: Ocular Prosthesis
definition: An Artificial Eye that is designed to replace a missing eye, but which does not function as an eye.

label: Thermal Imaging Artifact Function
definition: An Imaging Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to create a visual representation of an entity using radiation from the far infrared region of the electromagnetic spectrum that the entity emits

label: X-ray Telescope
definition: A Telescope that is designed to aid in the observation of spatially distant Objects by means of collecting and focusing X-rays to form an enhanced image of the Object.

label: Government Building
definition: A Facility that is designed for the administration of a community.

label: Temperature Measurement Artifact Function
definition: A Measurement Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to measure the Temperature of a specified object or class of objects.

label: Act Of Religious Worship
definition: An Act of Ceremony wherein there occurs acts of religious devotion usually directed towards a deity.

label: Act Of Consumption
definition: A Planned Act in which a resource is ingested or used up.

label: Act Of Maintenance
definition: An Act of Artifact Modification in which an Artifact is modified in order to preserve or restore one or more of its designed Qualities or Functions.

label: Electromagnetic Wave Process
definition: A Wave Process that is produced by charged particles, involves the periodic Oscillation of electric and magnetic fields at right angles to each other and the direction of wave propogation such that it has a Transverse Wave Profile, and which transfers electromagnetic radiant energy through a portion of space or matter.

label: Electric Motor
definition: An Engine that is designed to convert electrical energy into mechanical energy.

label: Pitch
definition: A Sound Process Profile that is characterized by the frequency of translated sound waves, typically on a continuum from low to high.

label: Telecommunication Infrastructure
definition: An Infrastructure System that is designed to support the use of Telecommunication Instruments to communicate.

label: Angular Momentum
definition: A Momentum that is the product of an object's moment of inertia and its Angular Velocity.

label: Highway Interchange
definition: A Road Junction that is designed to enable Ground Vehicles to exit one or more Highways and enter another Highway without directly crossing any other traffic stream.

label: Reservoir
definition: A Storage Facility that is designed to store water in a man-made open enclosure or area.

label: Information Content Entity
definition: A Generically Dependent Continuant that generically depends on some Information Bearing Entity and stands in relation of aboutness to some Entity.

label: Measurement Unit Of Frequency
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of the number of times an event repeats per unit of time.

label: Fixed Line Network Telephone Call
definition: A Telephone Call transmitted over a telephone network where the telephones are wired into a single telephone exchange.

label: Current Conversion Artifact Function
definition: An Electrical Artifact Function that is realized by processes in which some Artifact is used to convert some electrical current.

label: Portion Of Liquid Propellant
definition: A Portion of Propellant that is stored in a liquid state.

label: Fuel Transfer System
definition: A Fluid Control Artifact that is designed to facilitate the transfer of some Portion of Fuel from the Fuel Tank for use in some Engine.

label: Medium Frequency
definition: A Radio Frequency that is between 300 kHz and 3 MHz.

label: Directive Information Content Entity
definition: An Information Content Entity that consists of a set of propositions or images (as in the case of a blueprint) that prescribe some Entity.

label: Ean Barcode
definition: A One-Dimensional Barcode that consists of 8 or 13 numerical digits and is used to scan consumer goods.

label: Height
definition: A One Dimensional Extent that inheres in a bearer in virtue of the bearer's extension in a vertical direction.

label: Assault Rifle
definition: A Rifle that is designed to have selective-fire functionality and use an intermediate Cartridge and a detachable magazine.

label: Measurement Unit Of Speed
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of the rates at which objects traverse distance.

label: Act Of Artifact Modification
definition: An Act of Artifact Processing in which an existing Artifact is acted upon in a manner that changes, adds, or removes one or more of its Qualities, Dispositions, or Functions.

label: Act Of Deceptive Communication
definition: Ac Act of Communication intended to mislead the audience by distortion or falsification of evidence and induce a reaction that is prejudicial to the interests of the audience.

label: Ean-13 Barcode
definition: An EAN Barcode that consists of 13 numerical digits and is used to designate products at the point of sale.

label: Decimal Time Of Day Identifier
definition: A Time of Day Identifier that designates an approximate Temporal Instant that is part of some Day and is specified using a decimal value for the portion of the Day that preceded the Temporal Instant.

label: Plan
definition: A Directive Information Content Entity that prescribes some set of intended Intentional Acts through which some Agent expects to achieve some Objective.

label: Cyan
definition: A Color that is between Green and Blue with a wavelength in the visible spectrum typically between 490 and 520 nanometers.

label: Political Orientation
definition: An Ideology that characterizes the political thinking of an Agent or Group of Agents, usually with respect to the political environment within a particular nation.

label: Act Of Publishing Mass Media Documentary
definition: An Act of Mass Media Communication involving the preparation and public issuance of information that provides a factual record or report.

label: Cause
definition: A Process that is the cause of or one of the causes of some other Process.

label: Closure
definition: A Quality that inheres in a bearer in virtue of the degree to which that bearer affords passage or sightline through it via an opening, aperture, orifice, or vent.

label: Portion Of Waste Material
definition: A Portion of Processed Material that serves no further use in terms of the initial user's own purposes of production, transformation, or consumption such that the Agent wants to dispose of it.

label: Act Of Portion Of Material Consumption
definition: An Act of Artifact Employment in which a Portion of Material is expended.

label: Decrease Of Function
definition: A Decrease of Disposition in which some Independent Continuant has a decrease of some Function that it bears.

label: Shear Wave Process
definition: A Mechanical Wave that has a Transverse Wave Profile.

label: Occupation Role
definition: A Role that inheres in an Agent in virtue of the responsibilities that Agent is expected to fulfill within the context of some Act of Employment.

label: Thermal Insulation Artifact Function
definition: A Thermal Control Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact prevents or reduces the transfer of heat between objects that are in thermal contact or in range of radiative influence.

label: Scar
definition: A Bodily Component that consists of a portion of fibrous connective tissue on skin or within body tissue and which was formed due to an injury that has not healed completely.

label: Citizen Role
definition: A Role that inheres in a Person by virtue of that Person being legally recognized as a member of a particular state, with associated rights and obligations.

label: Reflective Prism
definition: A Prism designed to reflect light in order to flip, invert, rotate, deviate, or displace a beam of light entering the Prism.

label: Super High Frequency
definition: A Microwave Frequency that is between 3 and 30 GHz.

label: Nickname
definition: A Designative Name that is a familiar or humorous substitute for an entity's Proper Name.

label: Bent
definition: A Shape Quality inhering in a bearer in virtue of the bearer having one or more angles along its border.

label: Second
definition: A Temporal Interval that is equal to the duration of 9,192,631,770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the cesium 133 atom.

label: Power Rectifying Artifact Function
definition: A Current Conversion Artifact Function that is realized by processes in which some Artifact is used to convert alternating current (AC) to direct current (DC).

label: Electrical Power Production Artifact Function
definition: An Electrical Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to generate electrical power.

label: Material Artifact
definition: A Material Entity that was designed by some Agent to realize a certain Function.

label: Ramjet Engine
definition: An Air-Breathing Jet Engine that uses the forward motion of the Engine to compress incoming air (without the use of an axial compressor) and decelerate it to subsonic speeds before adding the fuel and constantly combusting the mixture then expelling the exhaust out through the rear Propelling Nozzle to generate Thrust.

label: Disrupting Disposition
definition: A disposition the realization of which would disrupt a process some entity has an interest in.

label: Telecommunication Network
definition: A Communication System that is designed to enable the transmission of information over significant distances between Telecommunication Endpoints via Telecommunication Network Nodes and Lines.

label: Defunct Stasis
definition: A Stasis of Artifact Operationality that holds during a Temporal Interval when an Artifact no longer maintains its designed set of Artifact Functions (or at least no longer maintains its primary functions).

label: Spray Nozzle
definition: A Nozzle that is designed to facilitate a conversion of the flow of a portion of liquid into a dynamic collection of drops dispersed in a portion of gas.

label: Drooping
definition: A Shape Quality inhering in a bearer in virtue of the bearer having a border that hangs downwards.

label: Message
definition: An Information Bearing Artifact that is designed to bear some specific Information Content Entity that is relatively brief and to be transmitted from a sender to a recipient.

label: Cartridge
definition: A Portion of Ammunition that is designed to package a Bullet, a propellant substance, and a primer within a case that is designed to fit within the firing chamber of a Firearm.

label: Measurement Unit Of Electromagnetic Force
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of the electromagnetic force between electrically charged entities.

label: Turbojet Air-breathing Jet Engine
definition: An Air-Breathing Jet Engine that uses a Turbojet, which consists of a Turbine with a Propelling Nozzle.

label: Operator Role
definition: A Role that inheres in an Agent by virtue of that Agent's responsibilities to operate or control some Artifact.

label: Passenger Train Car
definition: A Train Car that is designed to transport passengers.

label: Biological Weapon
definition: A Weapon that is designed to inflict harm, incapacity, or death by means of releasing disease-producing agents—such as bacteria, viruses, or fungi.

label: Optical Telescope
definition: A Telescope that is designed to aid in the observation of spatially distant Objects by means of collecting and focusing visible light to form an enhanced image of the Object.

label: Ordinal Measurement Information Content Entity
definition: A Measurement Information Content Entity that consists of a symbol that places an Entity into some rank order.

label: Automobile
definition: A Ground Motor Vehicle that is designed to transport a small number of passengers while traveling on four tired wheels.

label: Gs1 Databar Barcode
definition: A One-Dimensional Barcode that consists of 12-14 numerical digits and is used in retail and healthcare.

label: Heating Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized in a process in which the thermal energy of a system increases.

label: Proper Name
definition: A Designative Name that is an official name for a particular entity.

label: Controlled-access Highway
definition: A Highway that is designed for high-speed vehicular traffic, with all traffic flow and ingress/egress regulated.

label: Portion Of Lithosphere
definition: A fiat object part of the rigid, outermost rocky shell of a natural satellite.

label: Agent
definition: A Material Entity that bears an Agent Capability.

label: Equipment Cooling System
definition: A Cooling System that is designed to cool some piece of equipment.

label: Steering Control System
definition: A Vehicle Control System that is designed to control the direction some Vehicle is traveling.

label: Portion Of Gaseous Fuel
definition: A Portion of Fuel that is stored in a gaseous state.

label: Act Of Denying
definition: An Act of Representative Communication performed by either asserting that something is not true or real or refusing to satisfy a request or desire.

label: Ratio Measurement Information Content Entity
definition: A Measurement Information Content Entity that consists of a symbol that places a Quality of an Entity onto an interval scale having a true zero value.

label: Calendar Week
definition: A Week that begins and ends concurrently with the Days specified by a Calendar System to be the first and last Days of the Week.

label: Spark Ignition Engine
definition: An Internal Combustion Engine that is designed to operate by generating a spark to ignite a portion of Fuel and Oxidizer mixture.

label: Electric Generator
definition: An Electrical Power Source that is designed to convert mechanical energy to electrical energy for use in an external circuit.

label: Pointing Orientation
definition: A Spatial Orientation of a Material Entity in which one or more of its designated components are oriented toward a specified direction.

label: Trim Tab
definition: A Control Surface that is designed to counteract hydro-, aerodynamic, or other forces in order to stabilize the Vehicle it is part of in the desired Attitude.

label: Mechanical Wave Process
definition: A Wave Process that involves Oscillation of a portion of matter such that energy is transferred through the material medium.

label: Unguided Rocket
definition: A Portion of Ammunition that is designed to be a self-propelled, but unguided, projectile that delivers some payload (explosive or other) over relatively long distances through the use of a Rocket Engine.

label: Train
definition: A Rail Transport Vehicle that consists of a series of connected Train Cars or Railcars.

label: Act Of Volunteering
definition: An Act of Commissive Communication performed by voluntarily undertaking or expressing a willingness to undertake a service.

label: Act Of Assignment
definition: An Act of Declarative Communication in which rights held by one party (the assignor) are transferred to another party (the assignee) with regard to a particular entity as specified by the details of the assignment, which is often prescribed by a contract.

label: Biological Sex
definition: A Quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to undergo sexual reproduction in order to differentiate the individuals or types involved.

label: Full Motion Video Camera
definition: A Video Camera that is designed to capture and record images of sufficiently high quality and in rapid enough succession that the resulting video supports smooth playback.

label: Pitch Axis
definition: An Axis of Rotation that passes through the center of an object's Mass and is perpendicular both to the direction of the object's motion and to the object's Yaw Axis.

label: Communication System
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to enable some Act of Communication by means of transmission systems, relay stations, tributary stations, and data terminal equipment, usually capable of interconnection and interoperation to form an integrated whole.

label: Constructed Feature
definition: An Anthropogenic Feature that has been constructed by deliberate human effort.

label: Nickel Cadmium Electric Battery
definition: A Secondary Cell Electric Battery that has a cadmium anode and nickel oxide hydroxide cathode.

label: Act Of Repayment
definition: An Act of Financial Instrument Use wherein a Financial Instrument is transferred by an Agent (the Debtor) to another Agent (the Creditor) to decrease the amount the Debtor owes to the Creditor from an earlier Act of Loaning.

label: Nadir
definition: A One-Dimensional Spatial Region that extends from a given location downward along the local vertical direction pointing in the direction of the apparent Gravitational Force at that location.

label: Sequence Position Ordinality
definition: An Ordinal Measurement Information Content Entity that is about the position of some entity in some ordered sequence.

label: Equipment Mount
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to support an Artifact.

label: Aircraft
definition: A Vehicle that is designed to convey passengers, cargo, or equipment from one location to another by air travel.

label: Nuclear Radiation Detection Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to detect the presence of nuclear radiation particles.

label: Artifact Model
definition: A Directive Information Content Entity that prescribes a common set of Functions and Qualities to inhere in a set of artifact instances.

label: Notification Message
definition: A Message that is designed to bear an Information Content Entity that describes a scenario that has been determined to merit attention by the recipient.

label: Frequency
definition: A Process Profile that is characterized by the number of repetitive processes during a particular time period.

label: Increase Of Dependent Continuant
definition: A Change in which some Independent Continuant has an increase in the level of some Dependent Continuant that it bears.

label: Electrical Power Source
definition: A Power Source that is designed to generate, control, and transfer power in the form of electrical energy.

label: Primary Cell Electric Battery
definition: A Electric Battery that is designed for one-time use and not to be recharged.

label: Projectile Launcher
definition: A Weapon that is designed to inflict damage or harm by means of launching a high-velocity projectile at a target.

label: Military Facility
definition: A Facility that is designed to support a Military Force.

label: Act Of Collision
definition: An Act of Location Change involving the movement of one object such that it collides with another object.

label: Helical Antenna
definition: A Wire Antenna that consists of a conducting wire wound in the form of a helix that is typically mounted over a ground plane with a feed line connected between the bottom of the helix and the ground plane.

label: Branched
definition: A Shape Quality inhering in a bearer in virtue of the bearer having subdivisions or offshoots.

label: Visible Light Frequency
definition: An Electromagnetic Radiation Frequency of some Electromagnetic Wave that is between 400 and 800 terahertz.

label: Act Of Issuing Mass Media Press Release
definition: An Act of Mass Media Communication involving sending forth, distributing, or putting into circulation an official statement issued to one or more members of the media for the purpose of announcing newsworthy information.

label: Hour
definition: A Temporal Interval that is equal to sixty consecutive Minutes.

label: Shape Quality
definition: A Quality that inheres in a bearer in virtue of the ratios between dimensions of external features of that bearer.

label: Fuel System
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to pump, manage, and deliver some Portion of Fuel to the Propulsion System and Auxiliary Power Unit of some Vehicle.

label: Motorcycle
definition: A Ground Motor Vehicle that is designed to transport a very small number of passengers (usually 1 or 2) while traveling on two or three tired wheels.

label: International Community
definition: A maximal Group of Geopolitical Organizations engaged in geopolitics with one another.

label: Straight
definition: A Shape Quality inhering in a bearer in virtue of the bearer not having curves, bends, or angles along its borders.

label: Barcode
definition: An Information Bearing Artifact that is designed to bear one or more geometric shapes that concretize some Directive Information Content Entity.

label: Two Dimensional Extent
definition: A Size Quality that inheres in a bearer in virtue of the bearer's extension in two dimensions.

label: Loss Of Disposition
definition: A Loss of Realizable Entity in which some Independent Continuant ceases to be the bearer of some Disposition.

label: Laser
definition: A Material Artifact that is designed to emit light coherently through a process of optical amplification based on the stimulated emission of electromagnetic radiation.

label: Gain Of Quality
definition: A Gain of Specifically Dependent Continuant in which an Independent Continuant becomes the bearer of some Quality.

label: Representational Information Content Entity
definition: An Information Content Entity that represents some Entity.

label: Fluid Control Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized in processes in which some Artifact is used to control the direction or flow of some fluid.

label: Payload Capacity
definition: An Artifact Function that inheres in a Vehicle that is designed to transport Payload, and which is typically characterized by the maximum Weight, Mass, or Volume of Payload that the Vehicle can transport.

label: Fm Radio Broadcast Frequency
definition: A Very High Frequency that is between 88 and 108 MHz.

label: Financial Value Of Property
definition: Financial Value that inheres in an material entity that is the object of an Act of Ownership.

label: Act Of Educational Training Acquisition
definition: An Act of Training Acquisition performed by an Agent by acquiring knowledge of a curriculum from an Agent or communication medium that realizes a capacity derived from its affiliation with some Educational Organization.

label: Act Of Training Instruction
definition: An Act of Training performed by an Agent by imparting knowledge to another Agent.

label: Electric Power Station
definition: A Facility that is designed to generate electrical power.

label: Heavy Machine Gun
definition: A Mounted Gun that is designed to fire ammunition greater than .50 caliber or 12.7mm ammunition in quick succession from an ammunition belt, and which typically weighs more than 30lbs.

label: Airport
definition: A Transportation Facility that is designed for launching, receiving, and housing Aircraft.

label: Blond
definition: A Color that ranges from nearly white to a light greyish yellow

label: Far Infrared Light Frequency
definition: An Infrared Light Frequency that is between 300 gigahertz and 20 terahertz.

label: Geographic Feature
definition: An Environmental Feature that is a natural (i.e. not human made) topographical feature having a (relatively) stable location in some Geospatial Region which can be designated by location-specific data.

label: Patch Receiver
definition: A Radio Receiver that uses a Patch Antenna to intercept radio signals.

label: Air-breathing Combustion Engine
definition: A Reaction Engine that functions by drawing a continuous stream of air into and through the Engine where it is compressed, mixed with a Portion of Fuel, ignited, and then expelled as exhaust gas.

label: Portion Of Processed Material
definition: A Material Artifact that is the output of an Act of Artifact Processing.

label: Reflection Artifact Function
definition: An Artifact Function that is realized by an Artifact participating in a reflection event in which the Artifact causes a change in a wavefront at an interface between the reflecting medium and the transmission medium such that the wavefront returns into the transmission medium.

label: Road Junction
definition: A Land Transportation Artifact that is designed to enable Ground Vehicles to exit one Road and enter another.

label: Orientation Observation Artifact Function
definition: An Observation Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to collect information about the Orientation of a specified object or class of objects.

label: Decade
definition: A Temporal Interval that is equal to a period of ten consecutive Years.

label: Petrochemical Refinery
definition: A Refinery that is designed for refining crude oil, intermediate petroleum products, or synthetic petroleum into products of value.

label: Measurement Unit Of Pressure
definition: A Measurement Unit that is used as a standard for measurement of Force applied perpendicular to a surface per unit area.

label: Fort
definition: A Military Facility that is designed to support the defense of or solidification of rule over some Geospatial Region and its inhabitants.

label: Electrical Power Storage Artifact Function
definition: An Electrical Artifact Function that is realized during events in which an Artifact is used to store electrical power to be released at a later time.

label: Coin
definition: A Portion of Cash that consists of a flat, portable, round pieces of metal designed to bear some specified Financial Value.

label: Act Of Espionage
